37#define LOAD_KIND(kind) \
38 Int32Constant(static_cast<intptr_t>(LoadHandler::Kind::kind))
39#define STORE_KIND(kind) \
40 Int32Constant(static_cast<intptr_t>(StoreHandler::Kind::kind))

42// Loads dataX field from the DataHandler object.
43TNode<MaybeObject> AccessorAssembler::LoadHandlerDataField(
44 TNode<DataHandler> handler, int data_index) {
45#ifdef DEBUG
46 TNode<Map> handler_map = LoadMap(handler);
47 TNode<Uint16T> instance_type = LoadMapInstanceType(handler_map);
48#endif
49 CSA_DCHECK(this,
50 Word32Or(InstanceTypeEqual(instance_type, LOAD_HANDLER_TYPE),
51 InstanceTypeEqual(instance_type, STORE_HANDLER_TYPE)));
52 int offset = 0;
53 int minimum_size = 0;
54 switch (data_index) {
55 case 1:
56 offset = DataHandler::kData1Offset;
57 minimum_size = DataHandler::kSizeWithData1;
58 break;
59 case 2:
60 offset = DataHandler::kData2Offset;
61 minimum_size = DataHandler::kSizeWithData2;
62 break;
63 case 3:
64 offset = DataHandler::kData3Offset;
65 minimum_size = DataHandler::kSizeWithData3;
66 break;
67 default:
68 UNREACHABLE();
69 }
70 USE(minimum_size);
71 CSA_DCHECK(this, UintPtrGreaterThanOrEqual(
72 LoadMapInstanceSizeInWords(handler_map),
73 IntPtrConstant(minimum_size / kTaggedSize)));
74 return LoadMaybeWeakObjectField(handler, offset);
75}

77TNode<HeapObjectReference> AccessorAssembler::TryMonomorphicCase(
78 TNode<TaggedIndex> slot, TNode<FeedbackVector> vector,
79 TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_lookup_start_object_map, Label* if_handler,
80 TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_handler, Label* if_miss) {
81 Comment("TryMonomorphicCase");
82 DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, var_handler->rep());
83
84 // TODO(ishell): add helper class that hides offset computations for a series
85 // of loads.
86 int32_t header_size =
87 FeedbackVector::kRawFeedbackSlotsOffset - kHeapObjectTag;
88 // Adding |header_size| with a separate IntPtrAdd rather than passing it
89 // into ElementOffsetFromIndex() allows it to be folded into a single
90 // [base, index, offset] indirect memory access on x64.
91 TNode<IntPtrT> offset = ElementOffsetFromIndex(slot, HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
92 TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback = CAST(Load<MaybeObject>(
93 vector, IntPtrAdd(offset, IntPtrConstant(header_size))));
94
95 // Try to quickly handle the monomorphic case without knowing for sure
96 // if we have a weak reference in feedback.
97 CSA_DCHECK(this,
98 IsMap(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(weak_lookup_start_object_map)));
99 GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(feedback, weak_lookup_start_object_map), if_miss);
100
101 TNode<MaybeObject> handler = UncheckedCast<MaybeObject>(
102 Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), vector,
103 IntPtrAdd(offset, IntPtrConstant(header_size + kTaggedSize))));
104
105 *var_handler = handler;
106 Goto(if_handler);
107 return feedback;
108}

110void AccessorAssembler::HandlePolymorphicCase(
111 TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_lookup_start_object_map,
112 TNode<WeakFixedArray> feedback, Label* if_handler,
113 TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_handler, Label* if_miss) {
114 Comment("HandlePolymorphicCase");
115 DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, var_handler->rep());
116
117 // Iterate {feedback} array.
118 const int kEntrySize = 2;
119
120 // Load the {feedback} array length.
121 TNode<Int32T> length =
122 Signed(LoadAndUntagWeakFixedArrayLengthAsUint32(feedback));
123 CSA_DCHECK(this, Int32LessThanOrEqual(Int32Constant(kEntrySize), length));
124
125 // This is a hand-crafted loop that iterates backwards and only compares
126 // against zero at the end, since we already know that we will have at least a
127 // single entry in the {feedback} array anyways.
128 TVARIABLE(Int32T, var_index, Int32Sub(length, Int32Constant(kEntrySize)));
129 Label loop(this, &var_index), loop_next(this);
130 Goto(&loop);
131 BIND(&loop);
132 {
133 TNode<IntPtrT> index = ChangePositiveInt32ToIntPtr(var_index.value());
134 TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_cached_map =
135 LoadWeakFixedArrayElement(feedback, index);
136 CSA_DCHECK(this,
137 IsMap(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(weak_lookup_start_object_map)));
138 GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(maybe_cached_map, weak_lookup_start_object_map),
139 &loop_next);
140
141 // Found, now call handler.
142 TNode<MaybeObject> handler =
143 LoadWeakFixedArrayElement(feedback, index, kTaggedSize);
144 *var_handler = handler;
145 Goto(if_handler);
146
147 BIND(&loop_next);
148 var_index = Int32Sub(var_index.value(), Int32Constant(kEntrySize));
149 Branch(Int32GreaterThanOrEqual(var_index.value(), Int32Constant(0)), &loop,
150 if_miss);
151 }
152}

154void AccessorAssembler::TryMegaDOMCase(TNode<Object> lookup_start_object,
155 TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map,
156 TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_handler,
157 TNode<Object> vector,
158 TNode<TaggedIndex> slot, Label* miss,
159 ExitPoint* exit_point) {
160 // Check if the receiver is a JS_API_OBJECT
161 GotoIfNot(IsJSApiObjectMap(lookup_start_object_map), miss);
162
163 // Check if receiver requires access check
164 GotoIf(IsSetWord32<Map::Bits1::IsAccessCheckNeededBit>(
165 LoadMapBitField(lookup_start_object_map)),
166 miss);
167
168 CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedEqual(LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(vector), slot),
169 MegaDOMSymbolConstant()));
170
171 // In some cases, we load the
172 TNode<MegaDomHandler> handler;
173 if (var_handler->IsBound()) {
174 handler = CAST(var_handler->value());
175 } else {
176 TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_handler =
177 LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(vector), slot, kTaggedSize);
178 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsStrong(maybe_handler));
179 handler = CAST(maybe_handler);
180 }
181
182 // Check if dom protector cell is still valid
183 GotoIf(IsMegaDOMProtectorCellInvalid(), miss);
184
185 // Load the getter
186 TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_getter = LoadMegaDomHandlerAccessor(handler);
187 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_getter));
188 TNode<FunctionTemplateInfo> getter =
189 CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_getter, miss));
190
191 // Load the accessor context
192 TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_context = LoadMegaDomHandlerContext(handler);
193 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_context));
194 TNode<Context> context = CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_context, miss));
195
196 // TODO(gsathya): This builtin throws an exception on interface check fail but
197 // we should miss to the runtime.
198 TNode<Context> caller_context = context;
199 exit_point->Return(CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_Generic,
200 context, getter, Int32Constant(1),
201 caller_context, lookup_start_object));
202}

204void AccessorAssembler::TryEnumeratedKeyedLoad(
205 const LoadICParameters* p, TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map,
206 ExitPoint* exit_point) {
207 if (!p->IsEnumeratedKeyedLoad()) return;
208 Label no_enum_cache(this);
209 // |p->cache_type()| comes from the outer loop's ForIn state.
210 GotoIf(TaggedNotEqual(p->cache_type(), lookup_start_object_map),
211 &no_enum_cache);
212
213 // Use field index in EnumCache.
214 TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors =
215 LoadMapDescriptors(lookup_start_object_map);
216 TNode<EnumCache> enum_cache = LoadObjectField<EnumCache>(
217 descriptors, DescriptorArray::kEnumCacheOffset);
218 TNode<FixedArray> enum_keys =
219 LoadObjectField<FixedArray>(enum_cache, EnumCache::kKeysOffset);
220 // |p->enum_index()| comes from the outer loop's ForIn state.
221 TNode<Object> key = LoadFixedArrayElement(enum_keys, p->enum_index());
222 // Check if |p->name()| matches the key in enum cache. |p->name()| is the
223 // "each" variable of a for-in loop, but it can be modified by debugger or
224 // other bytecodes.
225 GotoIf(TaggedNotEqual(key, p->name()), &no_enum_cache);
226 TNode<FixedArray> enum_indices =
227 LoadObjectField<FixedArray>(enum_cache, EnumCache::kIndicesOffset);
228 // Check if we have enum indices available.
229 GotoIf(IsEmptyFixedArray(enum_indices), &no_enum_cache);
230 TNode<Int32T> field_index =
231 SmiToInt32(CAST(LoadFixedArrayElement(enum_indices, p->enum_index())));
232
233 TVARIABLE(Object, result);
234 Label if_double(this, Label::kDeferred), done(this, &result);
235 // Check if field is a mutable double field.
236 uint32_t kIsMutableDoubleFieldMask = 1;
237 GotoIf(IsSetWord32(field_index, kIsMutableDoubleFieldMask), &if_double);
238
239 TNode<Int32T> zero = Int32Constant(0);
240 {
241 Label if_outofobject(this);
242 // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object.
243 GotoIf(Int32LessThan(field_index, zero), &if_outofobject);
244
245 // The field is located in the {object} itself.
246 {
247 TNode<IntPtrT> offset = Signed(ChangeUint32ToWord(
248 Int32Add(Word32Shl(field_index, Int32Constant(kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)),
249 Int32Constant(JSObject::kHeaderSize))));
250 result =
251 LoadObjectField(CAST(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object()), offset);
252 Goto(&done);
253 }
254
255 // The field is located in the properties backing store of {object}.
256 // The {index} is equal to the negated out of property index plus 1.
257 BIND(&if_outofobject);
258 {
259 TNode<PropertyArray> properties = CAST(LoadFastProperties(
260 CAST(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object()), true));
261 TNode<IntPtrT> offset = Signed(ChangeUint32ToWord(Int32Add(
262 Word32Shl(Int32Sub(zero, field_index),
263 Int32Constant(kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)),
264 Int32Constant(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) - kTaggedSize))));
265 result = LoadObjectField(properties, offset);
266 Goto(&done);
267 }
268 }
269
270 // The field is a Double field, either unboxed in the object on 64-bit
271 // architectures, or a mutable HeapNumber.
272 BIND(&if_double);
273 {
274 TVARIABLE(Object, field);
275 Label loaded_field(this, &field), if_outofobject(this);
276 field_index = Word32Sar(field_index, Int32Constant(1));
277 // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object.
278 GotoIf(Int32LessThan(field_index, zero), &if_outofobject);
279
280 // The field is located in the {object} itself.
281 {
282 TNode<IntPtrT> offset = Signed(ChangeUint32ToWord(
283 Int32Add(Word32Shl(field_index, Int32Constant(kTaggedSizeLog2)),
284 Int32Constant(JSObject::kHeaderSize))));
285 field =
286 LoadObjectField(CAST(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object()), offset);
287 Goto(&loaded_field);
288 }
289
290 BIND(&if_outofobject);
291 {
292 TNode<PropertyArray> properties = CAST(LoadFastProperties(
293 CAST(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object()), true));
294 TNode<IntPtrT> offset = Signed(ChangeUint32ToWord(Int32Add(
295 Word32Shl(Int32Sub(zero, field_index),
296 Int32Constant(kTaggedSizeLog2)),
297 Int32Constant(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) - kTaggedSize))));
298 field = LoadObjectField(properties, offset);
299 Goto(&loaded_field);
300 }
301
302 BIND(&loaded_field);
303 {
304 // We may have transitioned in-place away from double, so check that
305 // this is a HeapNumber -- otherwise the load is fine and we don't need
306 // to copy anything anyway.
307 Label if_not_double(this);
308 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(field.value()), &if_not_double);
309
310 TNode<HeapObject> double_field = CAST(field.value());
311 TNode<Map> field_map = LoadMap(double_field);
312 GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(field_map, HeapNumberMapConstant()),
313 &if_not_double);
314
315 TNode<Float64T> value = LoadHeapNumberValue(double_field);
316 result = AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(value);
317 Goto(&done);
318
319 BIND(&if_not_double);
320 {
321 result = field.value();
322 Goto(&done);
323 }
324 }
325 }
326
327 BIND(&done);
328 { exit_point->Return(result.value()); }
329
330 BIND(&no_enum_cache);
331}

333void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadICHandlerCase(
334 const LazyLoadICParameters* p, TNode<MaybeObject> handler, Label* miss,
335 ExitPoint* exit_point, ICMode ic_mode, OnNonExistent on_nonexistent,
336 ElementSupport support_elements, LoadAccessMode access_mode) {
337 Comment("have_handler");
338
339 TVARIABLE(Object, var_holder, p->lookup_start_object());
340 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_smi_handler, handler);
341
342 Label if_smi_handler(this, {&var_holder, &var_smi_handler});
343 Label try_proto_handler(this, Label::kDeferred),
344 call_code_handler(this, Label::kDeferred),
345 call_getter(this, Label::kDeferred);
346
347 Branch(TaggedIsSmi(handler), &if_smi_handler, &try_proto_handler);
348
349 BIND(&try_proto_handler);
350 {
351 GotoIf(IsWeakOrCleared(handler), &call_getter);
352 GotoIf(IsCode(CAST(handler)), &call_code_handler);
353 HandleLoadICProtoHandler(p, CAST(handler), &var_holder, &var_smi_handler,
354 &if_smi_handler, miss, exit_point, ic_mode,
355 access_mode);
356 }
357
358 // |handler| is a Smi, encoding what to do. See SmiHandler methods
359 // for the encoding format.
360 BIND(&if_smi_handler);
361 {
362 HandleLoadICSmiHandlerCase(
363 p, var_holder.value(), CAST(var_smi_handler.value()), handler, miss,
364 exit_point, ic_mode, on_nonexistent, support_elements, access_mode);
365 }
366
367 BIND(&call_getter);
368 {
369 if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
370 exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
371 } else {
372 TNode<HeapObject> strong_handler = GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(handler, miss);
373 TNode<JSFunction> getter =
374 CAST(LoadAccessorPairGetter(CAST(strong_handler)));
375
376 ConvertReceiverMode mode =
377 p->lookup_start_object() == p->receiver()
378 // LoadIC case: the receiver is definitely not null or undefined.
379 ? ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined
380 // LoadSuperIC case: the receiver might be anything.
381 : ConvertReceiverMode::kAny;
382 exit_point->Return(
383 CallFunction(p->context(), getter, mode, p->receiver()));
384 }
385 }
386
387 BIND(&call_code_handler);
388 {
389 TNode<Code> code_handler = CAST(handler);
390 exit_point->ReturnCallStub(LoadWithVectorDescriptor{}, code_handler,
391 p->context(), p->lookup_start_object(),
392 p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
393 }
394}

396void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadCallbackProperty(
397 const LazyLoadICParameters* p, TNode<JSObject> holder,
398 TNode<Word32T> handler_word, ExitPoint* exit_point) {
399 Comment("native_data_property_load");
400 TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor =
401 Signed(DecodeWordFromWord32<LoadHandler::DescriptorBits>(handler_word));
402
403 TNode<AccessorInfo> accessor_info =
404 CAST(LoadDescriptorValue(LoadMap(holder), descriptor));
405
406 exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallApiGetter, p->context(),
407 p->receiver(), holder, accessor_info);
408}

410void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadAccessor(
411 const LazyLoadICParameters* p,
412 TNode<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template_info,
413 TNode<Word32T> handler_word, TNode<DataHandler> handler,
414 TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind, ExitPoint* exit_point) {
415 Comment("api_getter");
416 // Context is stored either in data2 or data3 field depending on whether
417 // the access check is enabled for this handler or not.
418 TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_context = Select<MaybeObject>(
419 IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::DoAccessCheckOnLookupStartObjectBits>(
420 handler_word),
421 [=, this] { return LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 3); },
422 [=, this] { return LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 2); });
423
424 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_context));
425 CSA_CHECK(this, IsNotCleared(maybe_context));
426 TNode<HeapObject> context = GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_context);
427
428 TVARIABLE(HeapObject, api_holder, CAST(p->lookup_start_object()));
429 Label load(this);
430 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kApiGetter)), &load);
431
432 CSA_DCHECK(this,
433 Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kApiGetterHolderIsPrototype)));
434
435 api_holder = LoadMapPrototype(LoadMap(CAST(p->lookup_start_object())));
436 Goto(&load);
437
438 BIND(&load);
439 {
440 TNode<Int32T> argc = Int32Constant(0);
441 TNode<Context> caller_context = p->context();
442 exit_point->Return(CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallApiCallbackGeneric, context,
443 argc, caller_context, function_template_info,
444 api_holder.value(), p->receiver()));
445 }
446}

448void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadField(TNode<JSObject> holder,
449 TNode<Word32T> handler_word,
450 TVariable<Float64T>* var_double_value,
451 Label* rebox_double, Label* miss,
452 ExitPoint* exit_point) {
453 Comment("LoadField");
454 TNode<IntPtrT> index =
455 Signed(DecodeWordFromWord32<LoadHandler::FieldIndexBits>(handler_word));
456 TNode<IntPtrT> offset = IntPtrMul(index, IntPtrConstant(kTaggedSize));
457
458 TNode<BoolT> is_inobject =
459 IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::IsInobjectBits>(handler_word);
460 TNode<HeapObject> property_storage = Select<HeapObject>(
461 is_inobject, [&]() { return holder; },
462 [&]() { return LoadFastProperties(holder, true); });
463
464 Label is_double(this);
465 TNode<Object> value = LoadObjectField(property_storage, offset);
466 GotoIf(IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::IsDoubleBits>(handler_word), &is_double);
467 exit_point->Return(value);
468
469 BIND(&is_double);
470 // This is not an "old" Smi value from before a Smi->Double transition.
471 // Rather, it's possible that since the last update of this IC, the Double
472 // field transitioned to a Tagged field, and was then assigned a Smi.
473 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(value), miss);
474 GotoIfNot(IsHeapNumber(CAST(value)), miss);
475 *var_double_value = LoadHeapNumberValue(CAST(value));
476 Goto(rebox_double);
477}

481void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadWasmField(
482 TNode<WasmObject> holder, TNode<Int32T> wasm_value_type,
483 TNode<IntPtrT> field_offset, TVariable<Float64T>* var_double_value,
484 Label* rebox_double, ExitPoint* exit_point) {
485 Label type_I8(this), type_I16(this), type_I32(this), type_U32(this),
486 type_I64(this), type_U64(this), type_F32(this), type_F64(this),
487 type_Ref(this), unsupported_type(this, Label::kDeferred),
488 unexpected_type(this, Label::kDeferred);
489 Label* wasm_value_type_labels[] = {
490 &type_I8, &type_I16, &type_I32, &type_U32, &type_I64,
491 &type_F32, &type_F64, &type_Ref, &type_Ref, &unsupported_type};
492 int32_t wasm_value_types[] = {
493 static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kI8),
494 static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kI16),
495 static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kI32),
496 static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kU32),
497 static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kI64),
498 static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kF32),
499 static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kF64),
500 static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kRef),
501 static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kRefNull),
502 // TODO(v8:11804): support the following value types.
503 static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kS128)};
504 const size_t kWasmValueTypeCount =
505 static_cast<size_t>(WasmValueType::kNumTypes);
506 DCHECK_EQ(kWasmValueTypeCount, arraysize(wasm_value_types));
507 DCHECK_EQ(kWasmValueTypeCount, arraysize(wasm_value_type_labels));
508
509 Switch(wasm_value_type, &unexpected_type, wasm_value_types,
510 wasm_value_type_labels, kWasmValueTypeCount);
511 BIND(&type_I8);
512 {
513 Comment("type_I8");
514 TNode<Int32T> value = LoadObjectField<Int8T>(holder, field_offset);
515 exit_point->Return(SmiFromInt32(value));
516 }
517 BIND(&type_I16);
518 {
519 Comment("type_I16");
520 TNode<Int32T> value = LoadObjectField<Int16T>(holder, field_offset);
521 exit_point->Return(SmiFromInt32(value));
522 }
523 BIND(&type_I32);
524 {
525 Comment("type_I32");
526 TNode<Int32T> value = LoadObjectField<Int32T>(holder, field_offset);
527 exit_point->Return(ChangeInt32ToTagged(value));
528 }
529 BIND(&type_U32);
530 {
531 Comment("type_U32");
532 TNode<Uint32T> value = LoadObjectField<Uint32T>(holder, field_offset);
533 exit_point->Return(ChangeUint32ToTagged(value));
534 }
535 BIND(&type_I64);
536 {
537 Comment("type_I64");
538 TNode<RawPtrT> data_pointer =
539 ReinterpretCast<RawPtrT>(BitcastTaggedToWord(holder));
540 TNode<BigInt> value = LoadFixedBigInt64ArrayElementAsTagged(
541 data_pointer,
542 Signed(IntPtrSub(field_offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag))));
543 exit_point->Return(value);
544 }
545 BIND(&type_F32);
546 {
547 Comment("type_F32");
548 TNode<Float32T> value = LoadObjectField<Float32T>(holder, field_offset);
549 *var_double_value = ChangeFloat32ToFloat64(value);
550 Goto(rebox_double);
551 }
552 BIND(&type_F64);
553 {
554 Comment("type_F64");
555 TNode<Float64T> value = LoadObjectField<Float64T>(holder, field_offset);
556 *var_double_value = value;
557 Goto(rebox_double);
558 }
559 BIND(&type_Ref);
560 {
561 Comment("type_Ref");
562 TNode<Object> value = LoadObjectField(holder, field_offset);
563 exit_point->Return(value);
564 }
565 BIND(&unsupported_type);
566 {
567 Print("Not supported Wasm field type");
568 Unreachable();
569 }
570 BIND(&unexpected_type);
571 { Unreachable(); }
572}

574void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadWasmField(
575 TNode<WasmObject> holder, TNode<Word32T> handler_word,
576 TVariable<Float64T>* var_double_value, Label* rebox_double,
577 ExitPoint* exit_point) {
578 Comment("LoadWasmField");
579 TNode<Int32T> wasm_value_type =
580 Signed(DecodeWord32<LoadHandler::WasmFieldTypeBits>(handler_word));
581 TNode<IntPtrT> field_offset = Signed(
582 DecodeWordFromWord32<LoadHandler::WasmFieldOffsetBits>(handler_word));
583
584 HandleLoadWasmField(holder, wasm_value_type, field_offset, var_double_value,
585 rebox_double, exit_point);
586}
587
588#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
589
590TNode<Object> AccessorAssembler::LoadDescriptorValue(
591 TNode<Map> map, TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor_entry) {
592 return CAST(LoadDescriptorValueOrFieldType(map, descriptor_entry));
593}
594
595TNode<MaybeObject> AccessorAssembler::LoadDescriptorValueOrFieldType(
596 TNode<Map> map, TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor_entry) {
597 TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors = LoadMapDescriptors(map);
598 return LoadFieldTypeByDescriptorEntry(descriptors, descriptor_entry);
599}
600
601void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadICSmiHandlerCase(
602 const LazyLoadICParameters* p, TNode<Object> holder, TNode<Smi> smi_handler,
603 TNode<MaybeObject> handler, Label* miss, ExitPoint* exit_point,
604 ICMode ic_mode, OnNonExistent on_nonexistent,
605 ElementSupport support_elements, LoadAccessMode access_mode) {
606 TVARIABLE(Float64T, var_double_value);
607 Label rebox_double(this, &var_double_value);
608
609 TNode<Int32T> handler_word = SmiToInt32(smi_handler);
610 TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind =
611 DecodeWord32<LoadHandler::KindBits>(handler_word);
612
613 if (support_elements == kSupportElements) {
614 Label if_element(this), if_indexed_string(this), if_property(this),
615 if_hole(this), unimplemented_elements_kind(this),
616 if_oob(this, Label::kDeferred), try_string_to_array_index(this),
617 emit_element_load(this);
618 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_intptr_index);
619 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kElement)), &if_element);
620
621 if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
622 CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32NotEqual(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kIndexedString)));
623 Goto(&if_property);
624 } else {
625 Branch(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kIndexedString)),
626 &if_indexed_string, &if_property);
627 }
628
629 BIND(&if_element);
630 {
631 Comment("element_load");
632 // TODO(ishell): implement
633 CSA_DCHECK(this,
634 IsClearWord32<LoadHandler::IsWasmArrayBits>(handler_word));
635 TVARIABLE(Int32T, var_instance_type);
636 TNode<IntPtrT> intptr_index = TryToIntptr(
637 p->name(), &try_string_to_array_index, &var_instance_type);
638 var_intptr_index = intptr_index;
639 Goto(&emit_element_load);
640
641 BIND(&try_string_to_array_index);
642 {
643 GotoIfNot(IsStringInstanceType(var_instance_type.value()), miss);
644
645 TNode<ExternalReference> function = ExternalConstant(
646 ExternalReference::string_to_array_index_function());
647 TNode<Int32T> result = UncheckedCast<Int32T>(
648 CallCFunction(function, MachineType::Int32(),
649 std::make_pair(MachineType::AnyTagged(), p->name())));
650 GotoIf(Word32Equal(Int32Constant(-1), result), miss);
651 CSA_DCHECK(this, Int32GreaterThanOrEqual(result, Int32Constant(0)));
652 var_intptr_index = ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(result);
653
654 Goto(&emit_element_load);
655 }
656
657 BIND(&emit_element_load);
658 {
659 TNode<BoolT> is_jsarray_condition =
660 IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::IsJsArrayBits>(handler_word);
661 TNode<Uint32T> elements_kind =
662 DecodeWord32<LoadHandler::ElementsKindBits>(handler_word);
663 EmitElementLoad(CAST(holder), elements_kind, var_intptr_index.value(),
664 is_jsarray_condition, &if_hole, &rebox_double,
665 &var_double_value, &unimplemented_elements_kind,
666 &if_oob, miss, exit_point, access_mode);
667 }
668 }
669
670 BIND(&unimplemented_elements_kind);
671 {
672 // Smi handlers should only be installed for supported elements kinds.
673 // Crash if we get here.
674 DebugBreak();
675 Goto(miss);
676 }
677
678 BIND(&if_oob);
679 {
680 Comment("out of bounds elements access");
681 Label return_undefined(this);
682
683 // Check if we're allowed to handle OOB accesses.
684 TNode<BoolT> allow_out_of_bounds =
685 IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::AllowOutOfBoundsBits>(handler_word);
686 GotoIfNot(allow_out_of_bounds, miss);
687
688 // Negative indices aren't valid array indices (according to
689 // the ECMAScript specification), and are stored as properties
690 // in V8, not elements. So we cannot handle them here, except
691 // in case of typed arrays, where integer indexed properties
692 // aren't looked up in the prototype chain.
693 GotoIf(IsJSTypedArray(CAST(holder)), &return_undefined);
694 if (Is64()) {
695 GotoIfNot(
696 UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(var_intptr_index.value(),
697 IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex)),
698 miss);
699 } else {
700 GotoIf(IntPtrLessThan(var_intptr_index.value(), IntPtrConstant(0)),
701 miss);
702 }
703
704 // For all other receivers we need to check that the prototype chain
705 // doesn't contain any elements.
706 BranchIfPrototypesHaveNoElements(LoadMap(CAST(holder)), &return_undefined,
707 miss);
708
709 BIND(&return_undefined);
710 exit_point->Return(access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas
711 ? TNode<Object>(FalseConstant())
712 : TNode<Object>(UndefinedConstant()));
713 }
714
715 BIND(&if_hole);
716 {
717 Comment("read hole and convert to undefined");
718
719 GotoIfNot(IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::AllowHandlingHole>(handler_word),
720 miss);
721 GotoIf(IsNoElementsProtectorCellInvalid(), miss);
722 exit_point->Return(access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas
723 ? TNode<Object>(FalseConstant())
724 : TNode<Object>(UndefinedConstant()));
725 }
726
727 if (access_mode != LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
728 BIND(&if_indexed_string);
729 {
730 Label if_oob_string(this, Label::kDeferred);
731
732 Comment("indexed string");
733 TNode<String> string_holder = CAST(holder);
734 TNode<IntPtrT> index = TryToIntptr(p->name(), miss);
735 TNode<UintPtrT> length =
736 Unsigned(LoadStringLengthAsWord(string_holder));
737 GotoIf(UintPtrGreaterThanOrEqual(index, length), &if_oob_string);
738 TNode<Int32T> code = StringCharCodeAt(string_holder, Unsigned(index));
739 TNode<String> result = StringFromSingleCharCode(code);
740 Return(result);
741
742 BIND(&if_oob_string);
743 if (Is64()) {
744 // Indices >= 4294967295 are stored as named properties; handle them
745 // in the runtime.
746 GotoIfNot(UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(
747 index, IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex)),
748 miss);
749 } else {
750 GotoIf(IntPtrLessThan(index, IntPtrConstant(0)), miss);
751 }
752 TNode<BoolT> allow_out_of_bounds =
753 IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::AllowOutOfBoundsBits>(handler_word);
754 GotoIfNot(allow_out_of_bounds, miss);
755 GotoIf(IsNoElementsProtectorCellInvalid(), miss);
756 Return(UndefinedConstant());
757 }
758 }
759
760 BIND(&if_property);
761 Comment("property_load");
762 }
763
764 if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
765 HandleLoadICSmiHandlerHasNamedCase(p, holder, handler_kind, miss,
766 exit_point, ic_mode);
767 } else {
768 HandleLoadICSmiHandlerLoadNamedCase(
769 p, holder, handler_kind, handler_word, &rebox_double, &var_double_value,
770 handler, miss, exit_point, ic_mode, on_nonexistent, support_elements);
771 }
772}
773
774void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadICSmiHandlerLoadNamedCase(
775 const LazyLoadICParameters* p, TNode<Object> holder,
776 TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind, TNode<Word32T> handler_word,
777 Label* rebox_double, TVariable<Float64T>* var_double_value,
778 TNode<MaybeObject> handler, Label* miss, ExitPoint* exit_point,
779 ICMode ic_mode, OnNonExistent on_nonexistent,
780 ElementSupport support_elements) {
781 Label constant(this), field(this), normal(this, Label::kDeferred),
782 slow(this, Label::kDeferred), interceptor(this, Label::kDeferred),
783 nonexistent(this), accessor(this, Label::kDeferred),
784 global(this, Label::kDeferred), module_export(this, Label::kDeferred),
785 proxy(this, Label::kDeferred),
786 native_data_property(this, Label::kDeferred),
787 api_getter(this, Label::kDeferred);
788
789 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kField)), &field);
790
791 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kConstantFromPrototype)),
792 &constant);
793
794 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kNonExistent)), &nonexistent);
795
796 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kNormal)), &normal);
797
798 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kAccessorFromPrototype)),
799 &accessor);
800
801 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kNativeDataProperty)),
802 &native_data_property);
803
804 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kApiGetter)), &api_getter);
805
806 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kApiGetterHolderIsPrototype)),
807 &api_getter);
808
809 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kGlobal)), &global);
810
811 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kSlow)), &slow);
812
813 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kProxy)), &proxy);
814
815 Branch(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kModuleExport)), &module_export,
816 &interceptor);
817
818 BIND(&field);
819 {
820#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
821 Label is_wasm_field(this);
822 GotoIf(IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::IsWasmStructBits>(handler_word),
823 &is_wasm_field);
824#else
825 CSA_DCHECK(this,
826 IsClearWord32<LoadHandler::IsWasmStructBits>(handler_word));
827#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
828
829 HandleLoadField(CAST(holder), handler_word, var_double_value, rebox_double,
830 miss, exit_point);
831
832#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
833 BIND(&is_wasm_field);
834 HandleLoadWasmField(CAST(holder), handler_word, var_double_value,
835 rebox_double, exit_point);
836#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
837 }
838
839 BIND(&nonexistent);
840 // This is a handler for a load of a non-existent value.
841 if (on_nonexistent == OnNonExistent::kThrowReferenceError) {
842 exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowReferenceError, p->context(),
843 p->name());
844 } else {
845 DCHECK_EQ(OnNonExistent::kReturnUndefined, on_nonexistent);
846 exit_point->Return(UndefinedConstant());
847 }
848
849 BIND(&constant);
850 {
851 Comment("constant_load");
852 exit_point->Return(holder);
853 }
854
855 BIND(&normal);
856 {
857 Comment("load_normal");
858 TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties =
859 CAST(LoadSlowProperties(CAST(holder)));
860 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_name_index);
861 Label found(this, &var_name_index);
862 NameDictionaryLookup<PropertyDictionary>(properties, CAST(p->name()),
863 &found, &var_name_index, miss);
864 BIND(&found);
865 {
866 TVARIABLE(Uint32T, var_details);
867 TVARIABLE(Object, var_value);
868 LoadPropertyFromDictionary<PropertyDictionary>(
869 properties, var_name_index.value(), &var_details, &var_value);
870 TNode<Object> value = CallGetterIfAccessor(
871 var_value.value(), CAST(holder), var_details.value(), p->context(),
872 p->receiver(), p->name(), miss);
873 exit_point->Return(value);
874 }
875 }
876
877 BIND(&accessor);
878 {
879 Comment("accessor_load");
880 // The "holder" slot (data1) in the from-prototype LoadHandler is instead
881 // directly the getter function.
882 TNode<HeapObject> getter = CAST(holder);
883 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsCallable(getter));
884
885 exit_point->Return(Call(p->context(), getter, p->receiver()));
886 }
887
888 BIND(&native_data_property);
889 HandleLoadCallbackProperty(p, CAST(holder), handler_word, exit_point);
890
891 BIND(&api_getter);
892 {
893 if (p->receiver() != p->lookup_start_object()) {
894 // Force super ICs using API getters into the slow path, so that we get
895 // the correct receiver checks.
896 Goto(&slow);
897 } else {
898 HandleLoadAccessor(p, CAST(holder), handler_word, CAST(handler),
899 handler_kind, exit_point);
900 }
901 }
902
903 BIND(&proxy);
904 {
905 // TODO(mythria): LoadGlobals don't use this path. LoadGlobals need special
906 // handling with proxies which is currently not supported by builtins. So
907 // for such cases, we should install a slow path and never reach here. Fix
908 // it to not generate this for LoadGlobals.
909 CSA_DCHECK(this,
910 WordNotEqual(IntPtrConstant(static_cast<int>(on_nonexistent)),
911 IntPtrConstant(static_cast<int>(
912 OnNonExistent::kThrowReferenceError))));
913 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_index);
914 TVARIABLE(Name, var_unique);
915
916 Label if_index(this), if_unique_name(this),
917 to_name_failed(this, Label::kDeferred);
918
919 if (support_elements == kSupportElements) {
920 DCHECK_NE(on_nonexistent, OnNonExistent::kThrowReferenceError);
921
922 TryToName(p->name(), &if_index, &var_index, &if_unique_name, &var_unique,
923 &to_name_failed);
924
925 BIND(&if_unique_name);
926 exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kProxyGetProperty, p->context(),
927 holder, var_unique.value(), p->receiver(),
928 SmiConstant(on_nonexistent));
929
930 BIND(&if_index);
931 // TODO(mslekova): introduce TryToName that doesn't try to compute
932 // the intptr index value
933 Goto(&to_name_failed);
934
935 BIND(&to_name_failed);
936 // TODO(duongn): use GetPropertyWithReceiver builtin once
937 // |lookup_element_in_holder| supports elements.
938 exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kGetPropertyWithReceiver,
939 p->context(), holder, p->name(),
940 p->receiver(), SmiConstant(on_nonexistent));
941 } else {
942 exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kProxyGetProperty, p->context(),
943 holder, p->name(), p->receiver(),
944 SmiConstant(on_nonexistent));
945 }
946 }
947
948 BIND(&global);
949 {
950 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsPropertyCell(CAST(holder)));
951 // Ensure the property cell doesn't contain the hole.
952 TNode<Object> value =
953 LoadObjectField(CAST(holder), PropertyCell::kValueOffset);
954 TNode<Uint32T> details = Unsigned(LoadAndUntagToWord32ObjectField(
955 CAST(holder), PropertyCell::kPropertyDetailsRawOffset));
956 GotoIf(IsPropertyCellHole(value), miss);
957
958 exit_point->Return(CallGetterIfAccessor(value, CAST(holder), details,
959 p->context(), p->receiver(),
960 p->name(), miss));
961 }
962
963 BIND(&interceptor);
964 {
965 Comment("load_interceptor");
966 exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadPropertyWithInterceptor,
967 p->context(), p->name(), p->receiver(),
968 holder, p->slot(), p->vector());
969 }
970 BIND(&slow);
971 {
972 Comment("load_slow");
973 if (ic_mode == ICMode::kGlobalIC) {
974 exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadGlobalIC_Slow, p->context(),
975 p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
976
977 } else {
978 exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kGetProperty, p->context(),
979 p->lookup_start_object(), p->name(),
980 p->receiver());
981 }
982 }
983
984 BIND(&module_export);
985 {
986 Comment("module export");
987 TNode<UintPtrT> index =
988 DecodeWordFromWord32<LoadHandler::ExportsIndexBits>(handler_word);
989 TNode<Module> module =
990 LoadObjectField<Module>(CAST(holder), JSModuleNamespace::kModuleOffset);
991 TNode<ObjectHashTable> exports =
992 LoadObjectField<ObjectHashTable>(module, Module::kExportsOffset);
993 TNode<Cell> cell = CAST(LoadFixedArrayElement(exports, index));
994 // The handler is only installed for exports that exist.
995 TNode<Object> value = LoadCellValue(cell);
996 Label is_the_hole(this, Label::kDeferred);
997 GotoIf(IsTheHole(value), &is_the_hole);
998 exit_point->Return(value);
999
1000 BIND(&is_the_hole);
1001 {
1002 TNode<Smi> message = SmiConstant(MessageTemplate::kNotDefined);
1003 exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowReferenceError, p->context(),
1004 message, p->name());
1005 }
1006 }
1007
1008 BIND(rebox_double);
1009 exit_point->Return(AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(var_double_value->value()));
1010}
1011
1012void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadICSmiHandlerHasNamedCase(
1013 const LazyLoadICParameters* p, TNode<Object> holder,
1014 TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind, Label* miss, ExitPoint* exit_point,
1015 ICMode ic_mode) {
1016 Label return_true(this), return_false(this), return_lookup(this),
1017 normal(this), global(this), slow(this);
1018
1019 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kField)), &return_true);
1020
1021 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kConstantFromPrototype)),
1022 &return_true);
1023
1024 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kNonExistent)), &return_false);
1025
1026 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kNormal)), &normal);
1027
1028 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kAccessorFromPrototype)),
1029 &return_true);
1030
1031 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kNativeDataProperty)),
1032 &return_true);
1033
1034 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kApiGetter)), &return_true);
1035
1036 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kApiGetterHolderIsPrototype)),
1037 &return_true);
1038
1039 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kSlow)), &slow);
1040
1041 Branch(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kGlobal)), &global,
1042 &return_lookup);
1043
1044 BIND(&return_true);
1045 exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
1046
1047 BIND(&return_false);
1048 exit_point->Return(FalseConstant());
1049
1050 BIND(&return_lookup);
1051 {
1052 CSA_DCHECK(this,
1053 Word32Or(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kInterceptor)),
1054 Word32Or(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kProxy)),
1055 Word32Equal(handler_kind,
1056 LOAD_KIND(kModuleExport)))));
1057 exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kHasProperty, p->context(),
1058 p->receiver(), p->name());
1059 }
1060
1061 BIND(&normal);
1062 {
1063 Comment("has_normal");
1064 TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties =
1065 CAST(LoadSlowProperties(CAST(holder)));
1066 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_name_index);
1067 Label found(this);
1068 NameDictionaryLookup<PropertyDictionary>(properties, CAST(p->name()),
1069 &found, &var_name_index, miss);
1070
1071 BIND(&found);
1072 exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
1073 }
1074
1075 BIND(&global);
1076 {
1077 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsPropertyCell(CAST(holder)));
1078 // Ensure the property cell doesn't contain the hole.
1079 TNode<Object> value =
1080 LoadObjectField(CAST(holder), PropertyCell::kValueOffset);
1081 GotoIf(IsPropertyCellHole(value), miss);
1082
1083 exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
1084 }
1085
1086 BIND(&slow);
1087 {
1088 Comment("load_slow");
1089 if (ic_mode == ICMode::kGlobalIC) {
1090 exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadGlobalIC_Slow, p->context(),
1091 p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
1092 } else {
1093 exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kHasProperty, p->context(),
1094 p->receiver(), p->name());
1095 }
1096 }
1097}
1098
1099// Performs actions common to both load and store handlers:
1100// 1. Checks prototype validity cell.
1101// 2. If |on_code_handler| is provided, then it checks if the sub handler is
1102// a smi or code and if it's a code then it calls |on_code_handler| to
1103// generate a code that handles Code handlers.
1104// If |on_code_handler| is not provided, then only smi sub handler are
1105// expected.
1106// 3. Does access check on lookup start object if
1107// ICHandler::DoAccessCheckOnLookupStartObjectBits bit is set in the smi
1108// handler.
1109// 4. Does dictionary lookup on receiver if
1110// ICHandler::LookupOnLookupStartObjectBits bit is set in the smi handler. If
1111// |on_found_on_lookup_start_object| is provided then it calls it to
1112// generate a code that handles the "found on receiver case" or just misses
1113// if the |on_found_on_lookup_start_object| is not provided.
1114// 5. Falls through in a case of a smi handler which is returned from this
1115// function (tagged!).
1116// TODO(ishell): Remove templatezation once we move common bits from
1117// Load/StoreHandler to the base class.
1118template <typename ICHandler, typename ICParameters>
1119TNode<Object> AccessorAssembler::HandleProtoHandler(
1120 const ICParameters* p, TNode<DataHandler> handler,
1121 const OnCodeHandler& on_code_handler,
1122 const OnFoundOnLookupStartObject& on_found_on_lookup_start_object,
1123 Label* miss, ICMode ic_mode) {
1124 //
1125 // Check prototype validity cell.
1126 //
1127 {
1128 TNode<Object> maybe_validity_cell =
1129 LoadObjectField(handler, ICHandler::kValidityCellOffset);
1130 CheckPrototypeValidityCell(maybe_validity_cell, miss);
1131 }
1132
1133 //
1134 // Check smi handler bits.
1135 //
1136 {
1137 TNode<Object> smi_or_code_handler =
1138 LoadObjectField(handler, ICHandler::kSmiHandlerOffset);
1139 if (on_code_handler) {
1140 Label if_smi_handler(this);
1141 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(smi_or_code_handler), &if_smi_handler);
1142 TNode<Code> code = CAST(smi_or_code_handler);
1143 on_code_handler(code);
1144
1145 BIND(&if_smi_handler);
1146 }
1147 TNode<IntPtrT> handler_flags = SmiUntag(CAST(smi_or_code_handler));
1148
1149 // Lookup on receiver and access checks are not necessary for global ICs
1150 // because in the former case the validity cell check guards modifications
1151 // of the global object and the latter is not applicable to the global
1152 // object.
1153 int mask = ICHandler::LookupOnLookupStartObjectBits::kMask |
1154 ICHandler::DoAccessCheckOnLookupStartObjectBits::kMask;
1155 if (ic_mode == ICMode::kGlobalIC) {
1156 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsClearWord(handler_flags, mask));
1157 } else {
1158 DCHECK_EQ(ICMode::kNonGlobalIC, ic_mode);
1159
1160 Label done(this), if_do_access_check(this),
1161 if_lookup_on_lookup_start_object(this);
1162 GotoIf(IsClearWord(handler_flags, mask), &done);
1163 // Only one of the bits can be set at a time.
1164 CSA_DCHECK(this,
1165 WordNotEqual(WordAnd(handler_flags, IntPtrConstant(mask)),
1166 IntPtrConstant(mask)));
1167 Branch(
1168 IsSetWord<typename ICHandler::DoAccessCheckOnLookupStartObjectBits>(
1169 handler_flags),
1170 &if_do_access_check, &if_lookup_on_lookup_start_object);
1171
1172 BIND(&if_do_access_check);
1173 {
1174 TNode<MaybeObject> data2 = LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 2);
1175 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(data2));
1176 TNode<Context> expected_native_context =
1177 CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(data2, miss));
1178 EmitAccessCheck(expected_native_context, p->context(),
1179 p->lookup_start_object(), &done, miss);
1180 }
1181
1182 BIND(&if_lookup_on_lookup_start_object);
1183 {
1184 // Dictionary lookup on lookup start object is not necessary for
1185 // Load/StoreGlobalIC (which is the only case when the
1186 // lookup_start_object can be a JSGlobalObject) because prototype
1187 // validity cell check already guards modifications of the global
1188 // object.
1189 CSA_DCHECK(this,
1190 Word32BinaryNot(HasInstanceType(
1191 CAST(p->lookup_start_object()), JS_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE)));
1192
1193 TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties =
1194 CAST(LoadSlowProperties(CAST(p->lookup_start_object())));
1195 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_name_index);
1196 Label found(this, &var_name_index);
1197 NameDictionaryLookup<PropertyDictionary>(
1198 properties, CAST(p->name()), &found, &var_name_index, &done);
1199 BIND(&found);
1200 {
1201 if (on_found_on_lookup_start_object) {
1202 on_found_on_lookup_start_object(properties, var_name_index.value());
1203 } else {
1204 Goto(miss);
1205 }
1206 }
1207 }
1208
1209 BIND(&done);
1210 }
1211 return smi_or_code_handler;
1212 }
1213}
1214
1215void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadICProtoHandler(
1216 const LazyLoadICParameters* p, TNode<DataHandler> handler,
1217 TVariable<Object>* var_holder, TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_smi_handler,
1218 Label* if_smi_handler, Label* miss, ExitPoint* exit_point, ICMode ic_mode,
1219 LoadAccessMode access_mode) {
1220 TNode<Smi> smi_handler = CAST(HandleProtoHandler<LoadHandler>(
1221 p, handler,
1222 // Code sub-handlers are not expected in LoadICs, so no |on_code_handler|.
1223 nullptr,
1224 // on_found_on_lookup_start_object
1225 [=, this](TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties,
1226 TNode<IntPtrT> name_index) {
1227 if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
1228 exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
1229 } else {
1230 TVARIABLE(Uint32T, var_details);
1231 TVARIABLE(Object, var_value);
1232 LoadPropertyFromDictionary<PropertyDictionary>(
1233 properties, name_index, &var_details, &var_value);
1234 TNode<Object> value = CallGetterIfAccessor(
1235 var_value.value(), CAST(var_holder->value()), var_details.value(),
1236 p->context(), p->receiver(), p->name(), miss);
1237 exit_point->Return(value);
1238 }
1239 },
1240 miss, ic_mode));
1241
1242 TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_holder_or_constant =
1243 LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 1);
1244
1245 Label load_from_cached_holder(this), is_smi(this), done(this);
1246
1247 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(maybe_holder_or_constant), &is_smi);
1248 Branch(TaggedEqual(maybe_holder_or_constant, NullConstant()), &done,
1249 &load_from_cached_holder);
1250
1251 BIND(&is_smi);
1252 {
1253 // If the "maybe_holder_or_constant" in the handler is a smi, then it's
1254 // guaranteed that it's not a holder object, but a constant value.
1255 CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<LoadHandler::KindBits>(
1256 SmiToInt32(smi_handler)),
1257 LOAD_KIND(kConstantFromPrototype)));
1258 if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
1259 exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
1260 } else {
1261 exit_point->Return(CAST(maybe_holder_or_constant));
1262 }
1263 }
1264
1265 BIND(&load_from_cached_holder);
1266 {
1267 // For regular holders, having passed the receiver map check and
1268 // the validity cell check implies that |holder| is
1269 // alive. However, for global object receivers, |maybe_holder| may
1270 // be cleared.
1271 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_holder_or_constant));
1272 TNode<HeapObject> holder =
1273 GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_holder_or_constant, miss);
1274 *var_holder = holder;
1275 Goto(&done);
1276 }
1277
1278 BIND(&done);
1279 {
1280 *var_smi_handler = smi_handler;
1281 Goto(if_smi_handler);
1282 }
1283}
1284
1285void AccessorAssembler::EmitAccessCheck(TNode<Context> expected_native_context,
1286 TNode<Context> context,
1287 TNode<Object> receiver,
1288 Label* can_access, Label* miss) {
1289 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsNativeContext(expected_native_context));
1290
1291 TNode<NativeContext> native_context = LoadNativeContext(context);
1292 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(expected_native_context, native_context), can_access);
1293 // If the receiver is not a JSGlobalProxy then we miss.
1294 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(receiver), miss);
1295 GotoIfNot(IsJSGlobalProxy(CAST(receiver)), miss);
1296 // For JSGlobalProxy receiver try to compare security tokens of current
1297 // and expected native contexts.
1298 TNode<Object> expected_token = LoadContextElement(
1299 expected_native_context, Context::SECURITY_TOKEN_INDEX);
1300 TNode<Object> current_token =
1301 LoadContextElement(native_context, Context::SECURITY_TOKEN_INDEX);
1302 Branch(TaggedEqual(expected_token, current_token), can_access, miss);
1303}
1304
1305void AccessorAssembler::JumpIfDataProperty(TNode<Uint32T> details,
1306 Label* writable, Label* readonly) {
1307 if (readonly) {
1308 // Accessor properties never have the READ_ONLY attribute set.
1309 GotoIf(IsSetWord32(details, PropertyDetails::kAttributesReadOnlyMask),
1310 readonly);
1311 } else {
1312 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsNotSetWord32(details,
1313 PropertyDetails::kAttributesReadOnlyMask));
1314 }
1315 TNode<Uint32T> kind = DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::KindField>(details);
1316 GotoIf(
1317 Word32Equal(kind, Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(PropertyKind::kData))),
1318 writable);
1319 // Fall through if it's an accessor property.
1320}
1321
1322void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreICNativeDataProperty(
1323 const StoreICParameters* p, TNode<HeapObject> holder,
1324 TNode<Word32T> handler_word) {
1325 Comment("native_data_property_store");
1326 TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor =
1327 Signed(DecodeWordFromWord32<StoreHandler::DescriptorBits>(handler_word));
1328 TNode<AccessorInfo> accessor_info =
1329 CAST(LoadDescriptorValue(LoadMap(holder), descriptor));
1330
1331 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreCallbackProperty, p->context(), p->receiver(),
1332 holder, accessor_info, p->name(), p->value());
1333}
1334
1335void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreICSmiHandlerJSSharedStructFieldCase(
1336 TNode<Context> context, TNode<Word32T> handler_word, TNode<JSObject> holder,
1337 TNode<Object> value) {
1338 CSA_DCHECK(this,
1339 Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word),
1340 STORE_KIND(kSharedStructField)));
1341 CSA_DCHECK(
1342 this,
1343 Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::RepresentationBits>(handler_word),
1344 Int32Constant(Representation::kTagged)));
1345
1346 TVARIABLE(Object, shared_value, value);
1347 SharedValueBarrier(context, &shared_value);
1348
1349 TNode<BoolT> is_inobject =
1350 IsSetWord32<StoreHandler::IsInobjectBits>(handler_word);
1351 TNode<HeapObject> property_storage = Select<HeapObject>(
1352 is_inobject, [&]() { return holder; },
1353 [&]() { return LoadFastProperties(holder, true); });
1354
1355 TNode<UintPtrT> index =
1356 DecodeWordFromWord32<StoreHandler::FieldIndexBits>(handler_word);
1357 TNode<IntPtrT> offset = Signed(TimesTaggedSize(index));
1358
1359 StoreSharedObjectField(property_storage, offset, shared_value.value());
1360
1361 // Return the original value.
1362 Return(value);
1363}
1364
1365void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreICHandlerCase(
1366 const StoreICParameters* p, TNode<MaybeObject> handler, Label* miss,
1367 ICMode ic_mode, ElementSupport support_elements) {
1368 Label if_smi_handler(this), if_nonsmi_handler(this);
1369 Label if_proto_handler(this), call_handler(this),
1370 store_transition_or_global_or_accessor(this);
1371
1372 Branch(TaggedIsSmi(handler), &if_smi_handler, &if_nonsmi_handler);
1373
1374 Label if_slow(this);
1375
1376 // |handler| is a Smi, encoding what to do. See SmiHandler methods
1377 // for the encoding format.
1378 BIND(&if_smi_handler);
1379 {
1380 TNode<Object> holder = p->receiver();
1381 TNode<Int32T> handler_word = SmiToInt32(CAST(handler));
1382
1383 Label if_fast_smi(this), if_proxy(this), if_interceptor(this);
1384
1385#define ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE(a, b) \
1386 static_assert(static_cast<intptr_t>(StoreHandler::Kind::a) + 1 == \
1387 static_cast<intptr_t>(StoreHandler::Kind::b));
1388 ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE(kGlobalProxy, kNormal)
1389 ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE(kNormal, kInterceptor)
1390 ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE(kInterceptor, kSlow)
1391 ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE(kSlow, kProxy)
1392 ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE(kProxy, kKindsNumber)
1393#undef ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE
1394
1395 TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind =
1396 DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word);
1397 GotoIf(Int32LessThan(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kGlobalProxy)), &if_fast_smi);
1398 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kProxy)), &if_proxy);
1399 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kInterceptor)),
1400 &if_interceptor);
1401 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kSlow)), &if_slow);
1402 CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kNormal)));
1403 TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties =
1404 CAST(LoadSlowProperties(CAST(holder)));
1405
1406 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_name_index);
1407 Label dictionary_found(this, &var_name_index);
1408 if (p->IsAnyDefineOwn()) {
1409 NameDictionaryLookup<PropertyDictionary>(properties, CAST(p->name()),
1410 &if_slow, nullptr, miss);
1411 } else {
1412 NameDictionaryLookup<PropertyDictionary>(properties, CAST(p->name()),
1413 &dictionary_found,
1414 &var_name_index, miss);
1415 }
1416
1417 // When dealing with class fields defined with DefineKeyedOwnIC or
1418 // DefineNamedOwnIC, use the slow path to check the existing property.
1419 if (!p->IsAnyDefineOwn()) {
1420 BIND(&dictionary_found);
1421 {
1422 Label if_constant(this), done(this);
1423 TNode<Uint32T> details =
1424 LoadDetailsByKeyIndex(properties, var_name_index.value());
1425 // Check that the property is a writable data property (no accessor).
1426 const int kTypeAndReadOnlyMask =
1427 PropertyDetails::KindField::kMask |
1428 PropertyDetails::kAttributesReadOnlyMask;
1429 static_assert(static_cast<int>(PropertyKind::kData) == 0);
1430 GotoIf(IsSetWord32(details, kTypeAndReadOnlyMask), miss);
1431
1432 if (V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL) {
1433 GotoIf(IsPropertyDetailsConst(details), miss);
1434 }
1435
1436 StoreValueByKeyIndex<PropertyDictionary>(
1437 properties, var_name_index.value(), p->value());
1438 Return(p->value());
1439 }
1440 }
1441 BIND(&if_fast_smi);
1442 {
1443 Label data(this), shared_struct_field(this), native_data_property(this);
1444 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kNativeDataProperty)),
1445 &native_data_property);
1446 Branch(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kSharedStructField)),
1447 &shared_struct_field, &data);
1448
1449 BIND(&native_data_property);
1450 HandleStoreICNativeDataProperty(p, CAST(holder), handler_word);
1451
1452 BIND(&shared_struct_field);
1453 HandleStoreICSmiHandlerJSSharedStructFieldCase(p->context(), handler_word,
1454 CAST(holder), p->value());
1455
1456 BIND(&data);
1457 // Handle non-transitioning field stores.
1458 HandleStoreICSmiHandlerCase(handler_word, CAST(holder), p->value(), miss);
1459 }
1460
1461 BIND(&if_proxy);
1462 {
1463 CSA_DCHECK(this, BoolConstant(!p->IsDefineKeyedOwn()));
1464 HandleStoreToProxy(p, CAST(holder), miss, support_elements);
1465 }
1466
1467 BIND(&if_interceptor);
1468 {
1469 Comment("store_interceptor");
1470 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStorePropertyWithInterceptor, p->context(),
1471 p->value(), p->receiver(), p->name());
1472 }
1473
1474 BIND(&if_slow);
1475 {
1476 Comment("store_slow");
1477 // The slow case calls into the runtime to complete the store without
1478 // causing an IC miss that would otherwise cause a transition to the
1479 // generic stub.
1480 if (ic_mode == ICMode::kGlobalIC) {
1481 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreGlobalIC_Slow, p->context(), p->value(),
1482 p->slot(), p->vector(), p->receiver(), p->name());
1483 } else {
1484 Runtime::FunctionId id;
1485 if (p->IsDefineNamedOwn()) {
1486 id = Runtime::kDefineNamedOwnIC_Slow;
1487 } else if (p->IsDefineKeyedOwn()) {
1488 id = Runtime::kDefineKeyedOwnIC_Slow;
1489 } else {
1490 id = Runtime::kKeyedStoreIC_Slow;
1491 }
1492 TailCallRuntime(id, p->context(), p->value(), p->receiver(), p->name());
1493 }
1494 }
1495 }
1496
1497 BIND(&if_nonsmi_handler);
1498 {
1499 TNode<HeapObjectReference> ref_handler = CAST(handler);
1500 GotoIf(IsWeakOrCleared(ref_handler),
1501 &store_transition_or_global_or_accessor);
1502 TNode<HeapObject> strong_handler = CAST(handler);
1503 TNode<Map> handler_map = LoadMap(strong_handler);
1504 Branch(IsCodeMap(handler_map), &call_handler, &if_proto_handler);
1505
1506 BIND(&if_proto_handler);
1507 {
1508 // Note, although DefineOwnICs don't reqiure checking for prototype
1509 // chain modifications the proto handlers shape is still used for
1510 // StoreHandler::StoreElementTransition in order to store both Code
1511 // handler and transition target map.
1512 HandleStoreICProtoHandler(p, CAST(strong_handler), &if_slow, miss,
1513 ic_mode, support_elements);
1514 }
1515
1516 // |handler| is a heap object. Must be code, call it.
1517 BIND(&call_handler);
1518 {
1519 TNode<Code> code_handler = CAST(strong_handler);
1520 TailCallStub(StoreWithVectorDescriptor{}, code_handler, p->context(),
1521 p->receiver(), p->name(), p->value(), p->slot(),
1522 p->vector());
1523 }
1524 }
1525
1526 BIND(&store_transition_or_global_or_accessor);
1527 {
1528 // Load value or miss if the {handler} weak cell is cleared.
1529 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(handler));
1530 TNode<HeapObject> strong_handler = GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(handler, miss);
1531
1532 Label store_global(this), store_transition(this), store_accessor(this);
1533 TNode<Map> strong_handler_map = LoadMap(strong_handler);
1534 GotoIf(IsPropertyCellMap(strong_handler_map), &store_global);
1535 Branch(IsAccessorPairMap(strong_handler_map), &store_accessor,
1536 &store_transition);
1537
1538 BIND(&store_global);
1539 {
1540 if (p->IsDefineKeyedOwn()) {
1541 Label proceed_defining(this);
1542 // StoreGlobalIC_PropertyCellCase doesn't support definition
1543 // of private fields, so handle them in runtime.
1544 GotoIfNot(IsSymbol(CAST(p->name())), &proceed_defining);
1545 Branch(IsPrivateName(CAST(p->name())), &if_slow, &proceed_defining);
1546 BIND(&proceed_defining);
1547 }
1548
1549 TNode<PropertyCell> property_cell = CAST(strong_handler);
1550 ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
1551 StoreGlobalIC_PropertyCellCase(property_cell, p->value(), &direct_exit,
1552 miss);
1553 }
1554 BIND(&store_accessor);
1555 {
1556 TNode<AccessorPair> pair = CAST(strong_handler);
1557 TNode<JSFunction> setter = CAST(LoadAccessorPairSetter(pair));
1558 // As long as this code path is not used for StoreSuperIC the receiver
1559 // is known to be neither undefined nor null.
1560 ConvertReceiverMode mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined;
1561 Return(
1562 CallFunction(p->context(), setter, mode, p->receiver(), p->value()));
1563 }
1564 BIND(&store_transition);
1565 {
1566 TNode<Map> map = CAST(strong_handler);
1567 HandleStoreICTransitionMapHandlerCase(p, map, miss,
1568 p->IsAnyDefineOwn()
1569 ? kDontCheckPrototypeValidity
1570 : kCheckPrototypeValidity);
1571 Return(p->value());
1572 }
1573 }
1574}
1575
1576void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreICTransitionMapHandlerCase(
1577 const StoreICParameters* p, TNode<Map> transition_map, Label* miss,
1578 StoreTransitionMapFlags flags) {
1579 DCHECK_EQ(0, flags & ~kStoreTransitionMapFlagsMask);
1580 if (flags & kCheckPrototypeValidity) {
1581 TNode<Object> maybe_validity_cell =
1582 LoadObjectField(transition_map, Map::kPrototypeValidityCellOffset);
1583 CheckPrototypeValidityCell(maybe_validity_cell, miss);
1584 }
1585
1586 TNode<Uint32T> bitfield3 = LoadMapBitField3(transition_map);
1587 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsClearWord32<Map::Bits3::IsDictionaryMapBit>(bitfield3));
1588 GotoIf(IsSetWord32<Map::Bits3::IsDeprecatedBit>(bitfield3), miss);
1589
1590 // Load last descriptor details.
1591 TNode<UintPtrT> nof =
1592 DecodeWordFromWord32<Map::Bits3::NumberOfOwnDescriptorsBits>(bitfield3);
1593 CSA_DCHECK(this, WordNotEqual(nof, IntPtrConstant(0)));
1594 TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors = LoadMapDescriptors(transition_map);
1595
1596 TNode<IntPtrT> factor = IntPtrConstant(DescriptorArray::kEntrySize);
1597 TNode<IntPtrT> last_key_index = UncheckedCast<IntPtrT>(IntPtrAdd(
1598 IntPtrConstant(DescriptorArray::ToKeyIndex(-1)), IntPtrMul(nof, factor)));
1599 if (flags & kValidateTransitionHandler) {
1600 TNode<Name> key = LoadKeyByKeyIndex(descriptors, last_key_index);
1601 GotoIf(TaggedNotEqual(key, p->name()), miss);
1602 } else {
1603 CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedEqual(LoadKeyByKeyIndex(descriptors, last_key_index),
1604 p->name()));
1605 }
1606 TNode<Uint32T> details = LoadDetailsByKeyIndex(descriptors, last_key_index);
1607 if (flags & kValidateTransitionHandler) {
1608 // Follow transitions only in the following cases:
1609 // 1) name is a non-private symbol and attributes equal to NONE,
1610 // 2) name is a private symbol and attributes equal to DONT_ENUM.
1611 Label attributes_ok(this);
1612 const int kKindAndAttributesDontDeleteReadOnlyMask =
1613 PropertyDetails::KindField::kMask |
1614 PropertyDetails::kAttributesDontDeleteMask |
1615 PropertyDetails::kAttributesReadOnlyMask;
1616 static_assert(static_cast<int>(PropertyKind::kData) == 0);
1617 // Both DontDelete and ReadOnly attributes must not be set and it has to be
1618 // a kData property.
1619 GotoIf(IsSetWord32(details, kKindAndAttributesDontDeleteReadOnlyMask),
1620 miss);
1621
1622 // DontEnum attribute is allowed only for private symbols and vice versa.
1623 Branch(Word32Equal(
1624 IsSetWord32(details, PropertyDetails::kAttributesDontEnumMask),
1625 IsPrivateSymbol(CAST(p->name()))),
1626 &attributes_ok, miss);
1627
1628 BIND(&attributes_ok);
1629 }
1630
1631 OverwriteExistingFastDataProperty(CAST(p->receiver()), transition_map,
1632 descriptors, last_key_index, details,
1633 p->value(), miss, true);
1634}
1635
1636void AccessorAssembler::UpdateMayHaveInterestingProperty(
1637 TNode<PropertyDictionary> dict, TNode<Name> name) {
1638 Comment("UpdateMayHaveInterestingProperty");
1639 Label done(this);
1640
1641 if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
1642 // TODO(pthier): Add flags to swiss dictionaries.
1643 Goto(&done);
1644 } else {
1645 GotoIfNot(IsInterestingProperty(name), &done);
1646 TNode<Smi> flags = GetNameDictionaryFlags(dict);
1647 flags = SmiOr(
1648 flags,
1649 SmiConstant(
1650 NameDictionary::MayHaveInterestingPropertiesBit::encode(true)));
1651 SetNameDictionaryFlags(dict, flags);
1652 Goto(&done);
1653 }
1654 BIND(&done);
1655}
1656
1657void AccessorAssembler::CheckFieldType(TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors,
1658 TNode<IntPtrT> name_index,
1659 TNode<Word32T> representation,
1660 TNode<Object> value, Label* bailout) {
1661 Label r_smi(this), r_double(this), r_heapobject(this), all_fine(this);
1662 GotoIf(Word32Equal(representation, Int32Constant(Representation::kSmi)),
1663 &r_smi);
1664 GotoIf(Word32Equal(representation, Int32Constant(Representation::kDouble)),
1665 &r_double);
1666 GotoIf(
1667 Word32Equal(representation, Int32Constant(Representation::kHeapObject)),
1668 &r_heapobject);
1669 GotoIf(Word32Equal(representation, Int32Constant(Representation::kNone)),
1670 bailout);
1671 CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32Equal(representation,
1672 Int32Constant(Representation::kTagged)));
1673 Goto(&all_fine);
1674
1675 BIND(&r_smi);
1676 { Branch(TaggedIsSmi(value), &all_fine, bailout); }
1677
1678 BIND(&r_double);
1679 {
1680 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(value), &all_fine);
1681 Branch(IsHeapNumber(CAST(value)), &all_fine, bailout);
1682 }
1683
1684 BIND(&r_heapobject);
1685 {
1686 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(value), bailout);
1687 TNode<MaybeObject> field_type =
1688 LoadFieldTypeByKeyIndex(descriptors, name_index);
1689 const Address kAnyType = FieldType::Any().ptr();
1690 // FieldType::Any can hold any value.
1691 GotoIf(
1692 TaggedEqual(field_type, BitcastWordToTagged(IntPtrConstant(kAnyType))),
1693 &all_fine);
1694 // FieldType::Class(...) performs a map check.
1695 // If the type is None we want this check to fail too, thus we compare the
1696 // maybe weak field type as is against a weak map ptr.
1697#ifdef DEBUG
1698 {
1699 // Check the field type is None or a weak map.
1700 Label check_done(this);
1701 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(field_type, BitcastWordToTagged(IntPtrConstant(
1702 FieldType::None().ptr()))),
1703 &check_done);
1704 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsMap(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(field_type)));
1705 Goto(&check_done);
1706 BIND(&check_done);
1707 }
1708#endif // DEBUG
1709 Branch(TaggedEqual(MakeWeak(LoadMap(CAST(value))), field_type), &all_fine,
1710 bailout);
1711 }
1712
1713 BIND(&all_fine);
1714}
1715
1716TNode<BoolT> AccessorAssembler::IsPropertyDetailsConst(TNode<Uint32T> details) {
1717 return Word32Equal(
1718 DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::ConstnessField>(details),
1719 Int32Constant(static_cast<int32_t>(PropertyConstness::kConst)));
1720}
1721
1722void AccessorAssembler::OverwriteExistingFastDataProperty(
1723 TNode<HeapObject> object, TNode<Map> object_map,
1724 TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors, TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor_name_index,
1725 TNode<Uint32T> details, TNode<Object> value, Label* slow,
1726 bool do_transitioning_store) {
1727 Label done(this), if_field(this), if_descriptor(this);
1728
1729 CSA_DCHECK(this,
1730 Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::KindField>(details),
1731 Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(PropertyKind::kData))));
1732
1733 Branch(Word32Equal(
1734 DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::LocationField>(details),
1735 Int32Constant(static_cast<int32_t>(PropertyLocation::kField))),
1736 &if_field, &if_descriptor);
1737
1738 BIND(&if_field);
1739 {
1740 TNode<Uint32T> representation =
1741 DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::RepresentationField>(details);
1742
1743 CheckFieldType(descriptors, descriptor_name_index, representation, value,
1744 slow);
1745
1746 TNode<UintPtrT> field_index =
1747 DecodeWordFromWord32<PropertyDetails::FieldIndexField>(details);
1748 field_index = Unsigned(
1749 IntPtrAdd(field_index,
1750 Unsigned(LoadMapInobjectPropertiesStartInWords(object_map))));
1751 TNode<IntPtrT> instance_size_in_words =
1752 LoadMapInstanceSizeInWords(object_map);
1753
1754 Label inobject(this), backing_store(this);
1755 Branch(UintPtrLessThan(field_index, instance_size_in_words), &inobject,
1756 &backing_store);
1757
1758 BIND(&inobject);
1759 {
1760 TNode<IntPtrT> field_offset = Signed(TimesTaggedSize(field_index));
1761 Label tagged_rep(this), double_rep(this);
1762 Branch(
1763 Word32Equal(representation, Int32Constant(Representation::kDouble)),
1764 &double_rep, &tagged_rep);
1765 BIND(&double_rep);
1766 {
1767 TNode<Float64T> double_value = ChangeNumberToFloat64(CAST(value));
1768 if (do_transitioning_store) {
1769 TNode<HeapNumber> heap_number =
1770 AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(double_value);
1771 StoreMap(object, object_map);
1772 StoreObjectField(object, field_offset, heap_number);
1773 } else {
1774 GotoIf(IsPropertyDetailsConst(details), slow);
1775 TNode<HeapNumber> heap_number =
1776 CAST(LoadObjectField(object, field_offset));
1777 StoreHeapNumberValue(heap_number, double_value);
1778 }
1779 Goto(&done);
1780 }
1781
1782 BIND(&tagged_rep);
1783 {
1784 if (do_transitioning_store) {
1785 StoreMap(object, object_map);
1786 } else {
1787 GotoIf(IsPropertyDetailsConst(details), slow);
1788 }
1789 StoreObjectField(object, field_offset, value);
1790 Goto(&done);
1791 }
1792 }
1793
1794 BIND(&backing_store);
1795 {
1796 TNode<IntPtrT> backing_store_index =
1797 Signed(IntPtrSub(field_index, instance_size_in_words));
1798
1799 if (do_transitioning_store) {
1800 // Allocate mutable heap number before extending properties backing
1801 // store to ensure that heap verifier will not see the heap in
1802 // inconsistent state.
1803 TVARIABLE(Object, var_value, value);
1804 {
1805 Label cont(this);
1806 GotoIf(Word32NotEqual(representation,
1807 Int32Constant(Representation::kDouble)),
1808 &cont);
1809 {
1810 TNode<Float64T> double_value = ChangeNumberToFloat64(CAST(value));
1811 TNode<HeapNumber> heap_number =
1812 AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(double_value);
1813 var_value = heap_number;
1814 Goto(&cont);
1815 }
1816 BIND(&cont);
1817 }
1818
1819 TNode<PropertyArray> properties =
1820 ExtendPropertiesBackingStore(object, backing_store_index);
1821 StorePropertyArrayElement(properties, backing_store_index,
1822 var_value.value());
1823 StoreMap(object, object_map);
1824 Goto(&done);
1825
1826 } else {
1827 Label tagged_rep(this), double_rep(this);
1828 TNode<PropertyArray> properties =
1829 CAST(LoadFastProperties(CAST(object), true));
1830 Branch(
1831 Word32Equal(representation, Int32Constant(Representation::kDouble)),
1832 &double_rep, &tagged_rep);
1833 BIND(&double_rep);
1834 {
1835 GotoIf(IsPropertyDetailsConst(details), slow);
1836 TNode<HeapNumber> heap_number =
1837 CAST(LoadPropertyArrayElement(properties, backing_store_index));
1838 TNode<Float64T> double_value = ChangeNumberToFloat64(CAST(value));
1839 StoreHeapNumberValue(heap_number, double_value);
1840 Goto(&done);
1841 }
1842 BIND(&tagged_rep);
1843 {
1844 GotoIf(IsPropertyDetailsConst(details), slow);
1845 StorePropertyArrayElement(properties, backing_store_index, value);
1846 Goto(&done);
1847 }
1848 }
1849 }
1850 }
1851
1852 BIND(&if_descriptor);
1853 {
1854 // Check that constant matches value.
1855 TNode<Object> constant =
1856 LoadValueByKeyIndex(descriptors, descriptor_name_index);
1857 GotoIf(TaggedNotEqual(value, constant), slow);
1858
1859 if (do_transitioning_store) {
1860 StoreMap(object, object_map);
1861 }
1862 Goto(&done);
1863 }
1864 BIND(&done);
1865}
1866
1867void AccessorAssembler::StoreJSSharedStructField(
1868 TNode<Context> context, TNode<HeapObject> shared_struct,
1869 TNode<Map> shared_struct_map, TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors,
1870 TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor_name_index, TNode<Uint32T> details,
1871 TNode<Object> maybe_local_value) {
1872 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsJSSharedStruct(shared_struct));
1873
1874 Label done(this);
1875
1876 TNode<UintPtrT> field_index =
1877 DecodeWordFromWord32<PropertyDetails::FieldIndexField>(details);
1878 field_index = Unsigned(IntPtrAdd(
1879 field_index,
1880 Unsigned(LoadMapInobjectPropertiesStartInWords(shared_struct_map))));
1881
1882 TNode<IntPtrT> instance_size_in_words =
1883 LoadMapInstanceSizeInWords(shared_struct_map);
1884
1885 TVARIABLE(Object, shared_value, maybe_local_value);
1886 SharedValueBarrier(context, &shared_value);
1887
1888 Label inobject(this), backing_store(this);
1889 Branch(UintPtrLessThan(field_index, instance_size_in_words), &inobject,
1890 &backing_store);
1891
1892 BIND(&inobject);
1893 {
1894 TNode<IntPtrT> field_offset = Signed(TimesTaggedSize(field_index));
1895 StoreSharedObjectField(shared_struct, field_offset, shared_value.value());
1896 Goto(&done);
1897 }
1898
1899 BIND(&backing_store);
1900 {
1901 TNode<IntPtrT> backing_store_index =
1902 Signed(IntPtrSub(field_index, instance_size_in_words));
1903
1904 CSA_DCHECK(
1905 this,
1906 Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::RepresentationField>(details),
1907 Int32Constant(Representation::kTagged)));
1908 TNode<PropertyArray> properties =
1909 CAST(LoadFastProperties(CAST(shared_struct), true));
1910 StoreJSSharedStructPropertyArrayElement(properties, backing_store_index,
1911 shared_value.value());
1912 Goto(&done);
1913 }
1914
1915 BIND(&done);
1916}

1934void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreICProtoHandler(
1935 const StoreICParameters* p, TNode<StoreHandler> handler, Label* slow,
1936 Label* miss, ICMode ic_mode, ElementSupport support_elements) {
1937 Comment("HandleStoreICProtoHandler");
1938
1939 OnCodeHandler on_code_handler;
1940 if (support_elements == kSupportElements) {
1941 // Code sub-handlers are expected only in KeyedStoreICs.
1942 on_code_handler = [=, this](TNode<Code> code_handler) {
1943 // This is either element store or transitioning element store.
1944 Label if_element_store(this), if_transitioning_element_store(this);
1945 Branch(IsStoreHandler0Map(LoadMap(handler)), &if_element_store,
1946 &if_transitioning_element_store);
1947 BIND(&if_element_store);
1948 {
1949 TailCallStub(StoreWithVectorDescriptor{}, code_handler, p->context(),
1950 p->receiver(), p->name(), p->value(), p->slot(),
1951 p->vector());
1952 }
1953
1954 BIND(&if_transitioning_element_store);
1955 {
1956 TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_transition_map =
1957 LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 1);
1958 TNode<Map> transition_map =
1959 CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_transition_map, miss));
1960
1961 GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(transition_map), miss);
1962
1963 TailCallStub(StoreTransitionDescriptor{}, code_handler, p->context(),
1964 p->receiver(), p->name(), transition_map, p->value(),
1965 p->slot(), p->vector());
1966 }
1967 };
1968 }
1969
1970 TNode<Object> smi_handler = HandleProtoHandler<StoreHandler>(
1971 p, handler, on_code_handler,
1972 // on_found_on_lookup_start_object
1973 [=, this](TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties,
1974 TNode<IntPtrT> name_index) {
1975 TNode<Uint32T> details = LoadDetailsByKeyIndex(properties, name_index);
1976 // Check that the property is a writable data property (no accessor).
1977 const int kTypeAndReadOnlyMask =
1978 PropertyDetails::KindField::kMask |
1979 PropertyDetails::kAttributesReadOnlyMask;
1980 static_assert(static_cast<int>(PropertyKind::kData) == 0);
1981 GotoIf(IsSetWord32(details, kTypeAndReadOnlyMask), miss);
1982
1983 StoreValueByKeyIndex<PropertyDictionary>(properties, name_index,
1984 p->value());
1985 Return(p->value());
1986 },
1987 miss, ic_mode);
1988
1989 {
1990 Label if_add_normal(this), if_store_global_proxy(this), if_api_setter(this),
1991 if_accessor(this), if_native_data_property(this);
1992
1993 CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedIsSmi(smi_handler));
1994 TNode<Int32T> handler_word = SmiToInt32(CAST(smi_handler));
1995
1996 TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind =
1997 DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word);
1998 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kNormal)), &if_add_normal);
1999
2000 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kSlow)), slow);
2001
2002 TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_holder = LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 1);
2003 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_holder));
2004 TNode<HeapObject> holder = GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_holder, miss);
2005
2006 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kGlobalProxy)),
2007 &if_store_global_proxy);
2008
2009 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kAccessorFromPrototype)),
2010 &if_accessor);
2011
2012 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kNativeDataProperty)),
2013 &if_native_data_property);
2014
2015 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kApiSetter)), &if_api_setter);
2016
2017 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kApiSetterHolderIsPrototype)),
2018 &if_api_setter);
2019
2020 CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kProxy)));
2021 HandleStoreToProxy(p, CAST(holder), miss, support_elements);
2022
2023 BIND(&if_add_normal);
2024 {
2025 // This is a case of "transitioning store" to a dictionary mode object
2026 // when the property does not exist. The "existing property" case is
2027 // covered above by LookupOnLookupStartObject bit handling of the smi
2028 // handler.
2029 Label slow(this);
2030 TNode<Map> receiver_map = LoadMap(CAST(p->receiver()));
2031 InvalidateValidityCellIfPrototype(receiver_map);
2032
2033 TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties =
2034 CAST(LoadSlowProperties(CAST(p->receiver())));
2035 TNode<Name> name = CAST(p->name());
2036 AddToDictionary<PropertyDictionary>(properties, name, p->value(), &slow);
2037 UpdateMayHaveInterestingProperty(properties, name);
2038 Return(p->value());
2039
2040 BIND(&slow);
2041 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kAddDictionaryProperty, p->context(),
2042 p->receiver(), p->name(), p->value());
2043 }
2044
2045 BIND(&if_accessor);
2046 {
2047 Comment("accessor_store");
2048 // The "holder" slot (data1) in the from-prototype StoreHandler is
2049 // instead directly the setter function.
2050 TNode<JSFunction> setter = CAST(holder);
2051
2052 // As long as this code path is not used for StoreSuperIC the receiver
2053 // is known to be neither undefined nor null.
2054 ConvertReceiverMode mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined;
2055 Return(
2056 CallFunction(p->context(), setter, mode, p->receiver(), p->value()));
2057 }
2058
2059 BIND(&if_native_data_property);
2060 HandleStoreICNativeDataProperty(p, holder, handler_word);
2061
2062 BIND(&if_api_setter);
2063 {
2064 Comment("api_setter");
2065 CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedIsNotSmi(handler));
2066 TNode<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template_info = CAST(holder);
2067
2068 // Context is stored either in data2 or data3 field depending on whether
2069 // the access check is enabled for this handler or not.
2070 TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_context = Select<MaybeObject>(
2071 IsSetWord32<StoreHandler::DoAccessCheckOnLookupStartObjectBits>(
2072 handler_word),
2073 [=, this] { return LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 3); },
2074 [=, this] { return LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 2); });
2075
2076 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_context));
2077 TNode<Object> context = Select<Object>(
2078 IsCleared(maybe_context), [=, this] { return SmiConstant(0); },
2079 [=, this] { return GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_context); });
2080
2081 TVARIABLE(Object, api_holder, p->receiver());
2082 Label store(this);
2083 GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kApiSetter)), &store);
2084
2085 CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32Equal(handler_kind,
2086 STORE_KIND(kApiSetterHolderIsPrototype)));
2087
2088 api_holder = LoadMapPrototype(LoadMap(CAST(p->receiver())));
2089 Goto(&store);
2090
2091 BIND(&store);
2092 {
2093 TNode<Int32T> argc = Int32Constant(1);
2094 TNode<Context> caller_context = p->context();
2095 Return(CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallApiCallbackGeneric, context, argc,
2096 caller_context, function_template_info,
2097 api_holder.value(), p->receiver(), p->value()));
2098 }
2099 }
2100
2101 BIND(&if_store_global_proxy);
2102 {
2103 ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
2104 // StoreGlobalIC_PropertyCellCase doesn't properly handle private names
2105 // but they are not expected here anyway.
2106 CSA_DCHECK(this, BoolConstant(!p->IsDefineKeyedOwn()));
2107 StoreGlobalIC_PropertyCellCase(CAST(holder), p->value(), &direct_exit,
2108 miss);
2109 }
2110 }
2111}
2112
2113void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreToProxy(const StoreICParameters* p,
2114 TNode<JSProxy> proxy, Label* miss,
2115 ElementSupport support_elements) {
2116 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_index);
2117 TVARIABLE(Name, var_unique);
2118
2119 Label if_index(this), if_unique_name(this),
2120 to_name_failed(this, Label::kDeferred);
2121
2122 if (support_elements == kSupportElements) {
2123 TryToName(p->name(), &if_index, &var_index, &if_unique_name, &var_unique,
2124 &to_name_failed);
2125
2126 BIND(&if_unique_name);
2127 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kProxySetProperty, p->context(), proxy,
2128 var_unique.value(), p->value(), p->receiver());
2129 Return(p->value());
2130
2131 // The index case is handled earlier by the runtime.
2132 BIND(&if_index);
2133 // TODO(mslekova): introduce TryToName that doesn't try to compute
2134 // the intptr index value
2135 Goto(&to_name_failed);
2136
2137 BIND(&to_name_failed);
2138 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kSetPropertyWithReceiver, p->context(), proxy,
2139 p->name(), p->value(), p->receiver());
2140 } else {
2141 TNode<Object> name = CallBuiltin(Builtin::kToName, p->context(), p->name());
2142 TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kProxySetProperty, p->context(), proxy, name,
2143 p->value(), p->receiver());
2144 }
2145}
