2147void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreICSmiHandlerCase(TNode<Word32T> handler_word,
2148 TNode<JSObject> holder,
2149 TNode<Object> value,
2150 Label* miss) {
2151 Comment("field store");
2152#ifdef DEBUG
2153 TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind =
2154 DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word);
2155 CSA_DCHECK(this,
2156 Word32Or(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kField)),
2157 Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kConstField))));
2158#endif
2159
2160 TNode<Uint32T> field_representation =
2161 DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::RepresentationBits>(handler_word);
2162
2163 Label if_smi_field(this), if_double_field(this), if_heap_object_field(this),
2164 if_tagged_field(this);
2165
2166 int32_t case_values[] = {Representation::kTagged, Representation::kHeapObject,
2167 Representation::kSmi};
2168 Label* case_labels[] = {&if_tagged_field, &if_heap_object_field,
2169 &if_smi_field};
2170
2171 Switch(field_representation, &if_double_field, case_values, case_labels, 3);
2172
2173 BIND(&if_tagged_field);
2174 {
2175 Comment("store tagged field");
2176 HandleStoreFieldAndReturn(handler_word, holder, value, std::nullopt,
2177 Representation::Tagged(), miss);
2178 }
2179
2180 BIND(&if_heap_object_field);
2181 {
2182 Comment("heap object field checks");
2183 CheckHeapObjectTypeMatchesDescriptor(handler_word, holder, value, miss);
2184
2185 Comment("store heap object field");
2186 HandleStoreFieldAndReturn(handler_word, holder, value, std::nullopt,
2187 Representation::HeapObject(), miss);
2188 }
2189
2190 BIND(&if_smi_field);
2191 {
2192 Comment("smi field checks");
2193 GotoIfNot(TaggedIsSmi(value), miss);
2194
2195 Comment("store smi field");
2196 HandleStoreFieldAndReturn(handler_word, holder, value, std::nullopt,
2197 Representation::Smi(), miss);
2198 }
2199
2200 BIND(&if_double_field);
2201 {
2202 CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32Equal(field_representation,
2203 Int32Constant(Representation::kDouble)));
2204 Comment("double field checks");
2205 TNode<Float64T> double_value = TryTaggedToFloat64(value, miss);
2206 CheckDescriptorConsidersNumbersMutable(handler_word, holder, miss);
2207
2208 Comment("store double field");
2209 HandleStoreFieldAndReturn(handler_word, holder, value, double_value,
2210 Representation::Double(), miss);
2211 }
2212}
2213
2214void AccessorAssembler::CheckHeapObjectTypeMatchesDescriptor(
2215 TNode<Word32T> handler_word, TNode<JSObject> holder, TNode<Object> value,
2216 Label* bailout) {
2217 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(value), bailout);
2218
2219 Label done(this);
2220 // Skip field type check in favor of constant value check when storing
2221 // to constant field.
2222 GotoIf(Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word),
2223 STORE_KIND(kConstField)),
2224 &done);
2225 TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor =
2226 Signed(DecodeWordFromWord32<StoreHandler::DescriptorBits>(handler_word));
2227 TNode<MaybeObject> field_type =
2228 LoadDescriptorValueOrFieldType(LoadMap(holder), descriptor);
2229
2230 const Address kAnyType = FieldType::Any().ptr();
2231 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(field_type, BitcastWordToTagged(IntPtrConstant(kAnyType))),
2232 &done);
2233 // Check that value type matches the field type.
2234 {
2235 // If the type is None we want this check to fail too, thus we compare the
2236 // maybe weak field type as is against a weak map ptr.
2237#ifdef DEBUG
2238 {
2239 // Check the field type is None or a weak map.
2240 Label check_done(this);
2241 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(field_type, BitcastWordToTagged(IntPtrConstant(
2242 FieldType::None().ptr()))),
2243 &check_done);
2244 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsMap(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(field_type)));
2245 Goto(&check_done);
2246 BIND(&check_done);
2247 }
2248#endif // DEBUG
2249 Branch(TaggedEqual(MakeWeak(LoadMap(CAST(value))), field_type), &done,
2250 bailout);
2251 }
2252 BIND(&done);
2253}
2254
2255void AccessorAssembler::CheckDescriptorConsidersNumbersMutable(
2256 TNode<Word32T> handler_word, TNode<JSObject> holder, Label* bailout) {
2257 // We have to check that the representation is Double. Checking the value
2258 // (either in the field or being assigned) is not enough, as we could have
2259 // transitioned to Tagged but still be holding a HeapNumber, which would no
2260 // longer be allowed to be mutable.
2261
2262 // TODO(leszeks): We could skip the representation check in favor of a
2263 // constant value check in HandleStoreFieldAndReturn here, but then
2264 // HandleStoreFieldAndReturn would need an IsHeapNumber check in case both the
2265 // representation changed and the value is no longer a HeapNumber.
2266 TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor_entry =
2267 Signed(DecodeWordFromWord32<StoreHandler::DescriptorBits>(handler_word));
2268 TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors = LoadMapDescriptors(LoadMap(holder));
2269 TNode<Uint32T> details =
2270 LoadDetailsByDescriptorEntry(descriptors, descriptor_entry);
2271
2272 GotoIfNot(IsEqualInWord32<PropertyDetails::RepresentationField>(
2273 details, Representation::kDouble),
2274 bailout);
2275}
2276
2277void AccessorAssembler::GotoIfNotSameNumberBitPattern(TNode<Float64T> left,
2278 TNode<Float64T> right,
2279 Label* miss) {
2280 // TODO(verwaest): Use a single compare on 64bit archs.
2281 const TNode<Uint32T> lhs_hi = Float64ExtractHighWord32(left);
2282 const TNode<Uint32T> rhs_hi = Float64ExtractHighWord32(right);
2283 GotoIfNot(Word32Equal(lhs_hi, rhs_hi), miss);
2284 const TNode<Uint32T> lhs_lo = Float64ExtractLowWord32(left);
2285 const TNode<Uint32T> rhs_lo = Float64ExtractLowWord32(right);
2286 GotoIfNot(Word32Equal(lhs_lo, rhs_lo), miss);
2287}
2288
2289void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreFieldAndReturn(
2290 TNode<Word32T> handler_word, TNode<JSObject> holder, TNode<Object> value,
2291 std::optional<TNode<Float64T>> double_value, Representation representation,
2292 Label* miss) {
2293 bool store_value_as_double = representation.IsDouble();
2294
2295 TNode<BoolT> is_inobject =
2296 IsSetWord32<StoreHandler::IsInobjectBits>(handler_word);
2297 TNode<HeapObject> property_storage = Select<HeapObject>(
2298 is_inobject, [&]() { return holder; },
2299 [&]() { return LoadFastProperties(holder, true); });
2300
2301 TNode<UintPtrT> index =
2302 DecodeWordFromWord32<StoreHandler::FieldIndexBits>(handler_word);
2303 TNode<IntPtrT> offset = Signed(TimesTaggedSize(index));
2304
2305 // For Double fields, we want to mutate the current double-value
2306 // field rather than changing it to point at a new HeapNumber.
2307 if (store_value_as_double) {
2308 TVARIABLE(HeapObject, actual_property_storage, property_storage);
2309 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, actual_offset, offset);
2310
2311 Label property_and_offset_ready(this);
2312
2313 // Store the double value directly into the mutable HeapNumber.
2314 TNode<Object> field = LoadObjectField(property_storage, offset);
2315 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsHeapNumber(CAST(field)));
2316 actual_property_storage = CAST(field);
2317 actual_offset = IntPtrConstant(offsetof(HeapNumber, value_));
2318 Goto(&property_and_offset_ready);
2319
2320 BIND(&property_and_offset_ready);
2321 property_storage = actual_property_storage.value();
2322 offset = actual_offset.value();
2323 }
2324
2325 // Do constant value check if necessary.
2326 Label do_store(this);
2327 GotoIfNot(Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word),
2328 STORE_KIND(kConstField)),
2329 &do_store);
2330 {
2331 if (store_value_as_double) {
2332 TNode<Float64T> current_value =
2333 LoadObjectField<Float64T>(property_storage, offset);
2334 GotoIfNotSameNumberBitPattern(current_value, *double_value, miss);
2335 Return(value);
2336 } else {
2337 TNode<Object> current_value = LoadObjectField(property_storage, offset);
2338 GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(current_value, value), miss);
2339 Return(value);
2340 }
2341 }
2342
2343 BIND(&do_store);
2344 // Do the store.
2345 if (store_value_as_double) {
2346 StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(property_storage, offset, *double_value);
2347 } else if (representation.IsSmi()) {
2348 TNode<Smi> value_smi = CAST(value);
2349 StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(property_storage, offset, value_smi);
2350 } else {
2351 StoreObjectField(property_storage, offset, value);
2352 }
2353
2354 Return(value);
2355}
2356
2357TNode<PropertyArray> AccessorAssembler::ExtendPropertiesBackingStore(
2358 TNode<HeapObject> object, TNode<IntPtrT> index) {
2359 Comment("[ Extend storage");
2360
2361 TVARIABLE(HeapObject, var_properties);
2362 TVARIABLE(Int32T, var_encoded_hash);
2363 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_length);
2364
2365 TNode<Object> properties =
2366 LoadObjectField(object, JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset);
2367
2368 Label if_smi_hash(this), if_property_array(this), extend_store(this);
2369 Branch(TaggedIsSmi(properties), &if_smi_hash, &if_property_array);
2370
2371 BIND(&if_smi_hash);
2372 {
2373 TNode<Int32T> hash = SmiToInt32(CAST(properties));
2374 TNode<Int32T> encoded_hash =
2375 Word32Shl(hash, Int32Constant(PropertyArray::HashField::kShift));
2376 var_encoded_hash = encoded_hash;
2377 var_length = IntPtrConstant(0);
2378 var_properties = EmptyFixedArrayConstant();
2379 Goto(&extend_store);
2380 }
2381
2382 BIND(&if_property_array);
2383 {
2384 var_properties = CAST(properties);
2385 TNode<Int32T> length_and_hash_int32 = LoadAndUntagToWord32ObjectField(
2386 var_properties.value(), PropertyArray::kLengthAndHashOffset);
2387 var_encoded_hash = Word32And(
2388 length_and_hash_int32, Int32Constant(PropertyArray::HashField::kMask));
2389 var_length = ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(
2390 Word32And(length_and_hash_int32,
2391 Int32Constant(PropertyArray::LengthField::kMask)));
2392 Goto(&extend_store);
2393 }
2394
2395 BIND(&extend_store);
2396 {
2397 TVARIABLE(HeapObject, var_new_properties, var_properties.value());
2398 Label done(this);
2399 // Previous property deletion could have left behind unused backing store
2400 // capacity even for a map that think it doesn't have any unused fields.
2401 // Perform a bounds check to see if we actually have to grow the array.
2402 GotoIf(UintPtrLessThan(index, ParameterToIntPtr(var_length.value())),
2403 &done);
2404
2405 TNode<IntPtrT> delta = IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kFieldsAdded);
2406 TNode<IntPtrT> new_capacity = IntPtrAdd(var_length.value(), delta);
2407
2408 // Grow properties array.
2409 DCHECK(kMaxNumberOfDescriptors + JSObject::kFieldsAdded <
2410 FixedArrayBase::GetMaxLengthForNewSpaceAllocation(PACKED_ELEMENTS));
2411 // The size of a new properties backing store is guaranteed to be small
2412 // enough that the new backing store will be allocated in new space.
2413 CSA_DCHECK(this, IntPtrLessThan(new_capacity,
2414 IntPtrConstant(kMaxNumberOfDescriptors +
2415 JSObject::kFieldsAdded)));
2416
2417 TNode<PropertyArray> new_properties = AllocatePropertyArray(new_capacity);
2418 var_new_properties = new_properties;
2419
2420 FillPropertyArrayWithUndefined(new_properties, var_length.value(),
2421 new_capacity);
2422
2423 // |new_properties| is guaranteed to be in new space, so we can skip
2424 // the write barrier.
2425 CopyPropertyArrayValues(var_properties.value(), new_properties,
2426 var_length.value(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER,
2427 DestroySource::kYes);
2428
2429 TNode<Int32T> new_capacity_int32 = TruncateIntPtrToInt32(new_capacity);
2430 TNode<Int32T> new_length_and_hash_int32 =
2431 Word32Or(var_encoded_hash.value(), new_capacity_int32);
2432 StoreObjectField(new_properties, PropertyArray::kLengthAndHashOffset,
2433 SmiFromInt32(new_length_and_hash_int32));
2434 StoreObjectField(object, JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset, new_properties);
2435 Comment("] Extend storage");
2436 Goto(&done);
2437 BIND(&done);
2438 return CAST(var_new_properties.value());
2439 }
2440}
2441
2442void AccessorAssembler::EmitFastElementsBoundsCheck(
2443 TNode<JSObject> object, TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements,
2444 TNode<IntPtrT> intptr_index, TNode<BoolT> is_jsarray_condition,
2445 Label* miss) {
2446 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_length);
2447 Comment("Fast elements bounds check");
2448 Label if_array(this), length_loaded(this, &var_length);
2449 GotoIf(is_jsarray_condition, &if_array);
2450 {
2451 var_length = LoadAndUntagFixedArrayBaseLength(elements);
2452 Goto(&length_loaded);
2453 }
2454 BIND(&if_array);
2455 {
2456 var_length = PositiveSmiUntag(LoadFastJSArrayLength(CAST(object)));
2457 Goto(&length_loaded);
2458 }
2459 BIND(&length_loaded);
2460 GotoIfNot(UintPtrLessThan(intptr_index, var_length.value()), miss);
2461}
2462
2463void AccessorAssembler::EmitElementLoad(
2464 TNode<HeapObject> object, TNode<Word32T> elements_kind,
2465 TNode<IntPtrT> intptr_index, TNode<BoolT> is_jsarray_condition,
2466 Label* if_hole, Label* rebox_double, TVariable<Float64T>* var_double_value,
2467 Label* unimplemented_elements_kind, Label* out_of_bounds, Label* miss,
2468 ExitPoint* exit_point, LoadAccessMode access_mode) {
2469 Label if_rab_gsab_typed_array(this), if_typed_array(this), if_fast(this),
2470 if_fast_packed(this), if_fast_holey(this), if_fast_double(this),
2471 if_fast_holey_double(this), if_nonfast(this), if_dictionary(this);
2472 Branch(Int32GreaterThan(elements_kind,
2473 Int32Constant(LAST_ANY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS_KIND)),
2474 &if_nonfast, &if_fast);
2475
2476 BIND(&if_fast);
2477 {
2478 TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadJSObjectElements(CAST(object));
2479 EmitFastElementsBoundsCheck(CAST(object), elements, intptr_index,
2480 is_jsarray_condition, out_of_bounds);
2481 int32_t kinds[] = {
2482 // Handled by if_fast_packed.
2483 PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS, PACKED_ELEMENTS, PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS,
2484 PACKED_SEALED_ELEMENTS, PACKED_FROZEN_ELEMENTS, SHARED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS,
2485 // Handled by if_fast_holey.
2486 HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS,
2487 HOLEY_FROZEN_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_SEALED_ELEMENTS,
2488 // Handled by if_fast_double.
2489 PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS,
2490 // Handled by if_fast_holey_double.
2491 HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS};
2492 Label* labels[] = {// FAST_{SMI,}_ELEMENTS
2493 &if_fast_packed, &if_fast_packed, &if_fast_packed,
2494 &if_fast_packed, &if_fast_packed, &if_fast_packed,
2495 // FAST_HOLEY_{SMI,}_ELEMENTS
2496 &if_fast_holey, &if_fast_holey, &if_fast_holey,
2497 &if_fast_holey, &if_fast_holey,
2498 // PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
2499 &if_fast_double,
2500 // HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
2501 &if_fast_holey_double};
2502 Switch(elements_kind, unimplemented_elements_kind, kinds, labels,
2503 arraysize(kinds));
2504
2505 BIND(&if_fast_packed);
2506 {
2507 Comment("fast packed elements");
2508 exit_point->Return(
2509 access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas
2510 ? TrueConstant()
2511 : UnsafeLoadFixedArrayElement(CAST(elements), intptr_index));
2512 }
2513
2514 BIND(&if_fast_holey);
2515 {
2516 Comment("fast holey elements");
2517 TNode<Object> element =
2518 UnsafeLoadFixedArrayElement(CAST(elements), intptr_index);
2519 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(element, TheHoleConstant()), if_hole);
2520 exit_point->Return(access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas ? TrueConstant()
2521 : element);
2522 }
2523
2524 BIND(&if_fast_double);
2525 {
2526 Comment("packed double elements");
2527 if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
2528 exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
2529 } else {
2530 *var_double_value =
2531 LoadFixedDoubleArrayElement(CAST(elements), intptr_index);
2532 Goto(rebox_double);
2533 }
2534 }
2535
2536 BIND(&if_fast_holey_double);
2537 {
2538 Comment("holey double elements");
2539 TNode<Float64T> value =
2540 LoadFixedDoubleArrayElement(CAST(elements), intptr_index, if_hole);
2541 if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
2542 exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
2543 } else {
2544 *var_double_value = value;
2545 Goto(rebox_double);
2546 }
2547 }
2548 }
2549
2550 BIND(&if_nonfast);
2551 {
2552 Label uint8_elements(this), int8_elements(this), uint16_elements(this),
2553 int16_elements(this), uint32_elements(this), int32_elements(this),
2554 float32_elements(this), float64_elements(this), bigint64_elements(this),
2555 biguint64_elements(this), float16_elements(this);
2556 static_assert(LAST_ELEMENTS_KIND ==
2557 LAST_RAB_GSAB_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND);
2558 GotoIf(Int32GreaterThanOrEqual(
2559 elements_kind,
2560 Int32Constant(FIRST_RAB_GSAB_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND)),
2561 &if_rab_gsab_typed_array);
2562 GotoIf(Int32GreaterThanOrEqual(
2563 elements_kind,
2564 Int32Constant(FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND)),
2565 &if_typed_array);
2566 GotoIf(Word32Equal(elements_kind, Int32Constant(DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS)),
2567 &if_dictionary);
2568 Goto(unimplemented_elements_kind);
2569
2570 BIND(&if_dictionary);
2571 {
2572 Comment("dictionary elements");
2573 if (Is64()) {
2574 GotoIf(UintPtrLessThan(IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex),
2575 intptr_index),
2576 out_of_bounds);
2577 } else {
2578 GotoIf(IntPtrLessThan(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(0)), out_of_bounds);
2579 }
2580
2581 TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadJSObjectElements(CAST(object));
2582 TNode<Object> value = BasicLoadNumberDictionaryElement(
2583 CAST(elements), intptr_index, miss, if_hole);
2584 exit_point->Return(access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas ? TrueConstant()
2585 : value);
2586 }
2587 {
2588 TVARIABLE(RawPtrT, data_ptr);
2589 BIND(&if_rab_gsab_typed_array);
2590 {
2591 Comment("rab gsab typed elements");
2592 Label variable_length(this), normal(this), length_check_ok(this);
2593
2594 TNode<JSTypedArray> array = CAST(object);
2595 TNode<JSArrayBuffer> buffer = LoadJSArrayBufferViewBuffer(array);
2596
2597 // Bounds check (incl. detachedness check).
2598 TNode<UintPtrT> length =
2599 LoadVariableLengthJSTypedArrayLength(array, buffer, miss);
2600 Branch(UintPtrLessThan(intptr_index, length), &length_check_ok,
2601 out_of_bounds);
2602 BIND(&length_check_ok);
2603 {
2604 if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
2605 exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
2606 } else {
2607 data_ptr = LoadJSTypedArrayDataPtr(array);
2608 Label* elements_kind_labels[] = {
2609 &uint8_elements, &uint8_elements, &int8_elements,
2610 &uint16_elements, &int16_elements, &uint32_elements,
2611 &int32_elements, &float32_elements, &float64_elements,
2612 &bigint64_elements, &biguint64_elements, &float16_elements,
2613 };
2614 int32_t elements_kinds[] = {
2615 RAB_GSAB_UINT8_ELEMENTS, RAB_GSAB_UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS,
2616 RAB_GSAB_INT8_ELEMENTS, RAB_GSAB_UINT16_ELEMENTS,
2617 RAB_GSAB_INT16_ELEMENTS, RAB_GSAB_UINT32_ELEMENTS,
2618 RAB_GSAB_INT32_ELEMENTS, RAB_GSAB_FLOAT32_ELEMENTS,
2619 RAB_GSAB_FLOAT64_ELEMENTS, RAB_GSAB_BIGINT64_ELEMENTS,
2620 RAB_GSAB_BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS, RAB_GSAB_FLOAT16_ELEMENTS};
2621 const size_t kTypedElementsKindCount =
2622 LAST_RAB_GSAB_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND -
2623 FIRST_RAB_GSAB_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND + 1;
2624 DCHECK_EQ(kTypedElementsKindCount, arraysize(elements_kinds));
2625 DCHECK_EQ(kTypedElementsKindCount, arraysize(elements_kind_labels));
2626 Switch(elements_kind, miss, elements_kinds, elements_kind_labels,
2627 kTypedElementsKindCount);
2628 }
2629 }
2630 }
2631 BIND(&if_typed_array);
2632 {
2633 Comment("typed elements");
2634 // Check if buffer has been detached.
2635 TNode<JSArrayBuffer> buffer = LoadJSArrayBufferViewBuffer(CAST(object));
2636 GotoIf(IsDetachedBuffer(buffer), miss);
2637
2638 // Bounds check.
2639 TNode<UintPtrT> length = LoadJSTypedArrayLength(CAST(object));
2640 GotoIfNot(UintPtrLessThan(intptr_index, length), out_of_bounds);
2641 if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
2642 exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
2643 } else {
2644 data_ptr = LoadJSTypedArrayDataPtr(CAST(object));
2645
2646 Label* elements_kind_labels[] = {
2647 &uint8_elements, &uint8_elements, &int8_elements,
2648 &uint16_elements, &int16_elements, &uint32_elements,
2649 &int32_elements, &float32_elements, &float64_elements,
2650 &bigint64_elements, &biguint64_elements, &float16_elements};
2651 int32_t elements_kinds[] = {
2652 UINT8_ELEMENTS, UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS, INT8_ELEMENTS,
2653 UINT16_ELEMENTS, INT16_ELEMENTS, UINT32_ELEMENTS,
2654 INT32_ELEMENTS, FLOAT32_ELEMENTS, FLOAT64_ELEMENTS,
2655 BIGINT64_ELEMENTS, BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS, FLOAT16_ELEMENTS};
2656 const size_t kTypedElementsKindCount =
2657 LAST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND -
2658 FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND + 1;
2659 DCHECK_EQ(kTypedElementsKindCount, arraysize(elements_kinds));
2660 DCHECK_EQ(kTypedElementsKindCount, arraysize(elements_kind_labels));
2661 Switch(elements_kind, miss, elements_kinds, elements_kind_labels,
2662 kTypedElementsKindCount);
2663 }
2664 }
2665 if (access_mode != LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
2666 BIND(&uint8_elements);
2667 {
2668 Comment("UINT8_ELEMENTS"); // Handles UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS too.
2669 TNode<Int32T> element = Load<Uint8T>(data_ptr.value(), intptr_index);
2670 exit_point->Return(SmiFromInt32(element));
2671 }
2672 BIND(&int8_elements);
2673 {
2674 Comment("INT8_ELEMENTS");
2675 TNode<Int32T> element = Load<Int8T>(data_ptr.value(), intptr_index);
2676 exit_point->Return(SmiFromInt32(element));
2677 }
2678 BIND(&uint16_elements);
2679 {
2680 Comment("UINT16_ELEMENTS");
2681 TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(1));
2682 TNode<Int32T> element = Load<Uint16T>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2683 exit_point->Return(SmiFromInt32(element));
2684 }
2685 BIND(&int16_elements);
2686 {
2687 Comment("INT16_ELEMENTS");
2688 TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(1));
2689 TNode<Int32T> element = Load<Int16T>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2690 exit_point->Return(SmiFromInt32(element));
2691 }
2692 BIND(&uint32_elements);
2693 {
2694 Comment("UINT32_ELEMENTS");
2695 TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(2));
2696 TNode<Uint32T> element = Load<Uint32T>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2697 exit_point->Return(ChangeUint32ToTagged(element));
2698 }
2699 BIND(&int32_elements);
2700 {
2701 Comment("INT32_ELEMENTS");
2702 TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(2));
2703 TNode<Int32T> element = Load<Int32T>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2704 exit_point->Return(ChangeInt32ToTagged(element));
2705 }
2706 BIND(&float16_elements);
2707 {
2708 Comment("FLOAT16_ELEMENTS");
2709 TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(1));
2710 TNode<Float16RawBitsT> raw_element =
2711 Load<Float16RawBitsT>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2712 *var_double_value = ChangeFloat16ToFloat64(raw_element);
2713 Goto(rebox_double);
2714 }
2715 BIND(&float32_elements);
2716 {
2717 Comment("FLOAT32_ELEMENTS");
2718 TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(2));
2719 TNode<Float32T> element = Load<Float32T>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2720 *var_double_value = ChangeFloat32ToFloat64(element);
2721 Goto(rebox_double);
2722 }
2723 BIND(&float64_elements);
2724 {
2725 Comment("FLOAT64_ELEMENTS");
2726 TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(3));
2727 TNode<Float64T> element = Load<Float64T>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2728 *var_double_value = element;
2729 Goto(rebox_double);
2730 }
2731 BIND(&bigint64_elements);
2732 {
2733 Comment("BIGINT64_ELEMENTS");
2734 exit_point->Return(LoadFixedTypedArrayElementAsTagged(
2735 data_ptr.value(), Unsigned(intptr_index), BIGINT64_ELEMENTS));
2736 }
2737 BIND(&biguint64_elements);
2738 {
2739 Comment("BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS");
2740 exit_point->Return(LoadFixedTypedArrayElementAsTagged(
2741 data_ptr.value(), Unsigned(intptr_index), BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS));
2742 }
2743 }
2744 }
2745 }
2746}
2747
2748void AccessorAssembler::InvalidateValidityCellIfPrototype(
2749 TNode<Map> map, std::optional<TNode<Uint32T>> maybe_bitfield3) {
2750 Label is_prototype(this), cont(this);
2751 TNode<Uint32T> bitfield3;
2752 if (maybe_bitfield3) {
2753 bitfield3 = maybe_bitfield3.value();
2754 } else {
2755 bitfield3 = LoadMapBitField3(map);
2756 }
2757
2758 Branch(IsSetWord32(bitfield3, Map::Bits3::IsPrototypeMapBit::kMask),
2759 &is_prototype, &cont);
2760
2761 BIND(&is_prototype);
2762 {
2763 TNode<Object> maybe_prototype_info =
2764 LoadObjectField(map, Map::kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset);
2765 // If there's no prototype info then there's nothing to invalidate.
2766 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(maybe_prototype_info), &cont);
2767
2768 TNode<ExternalReference> function = ExternalConstant(
2769 ExternalReference::invalidate_prototype_chains_function());
2770 CallCFunction(function, MachineType::AnyTagged(),
2771 std::make_pair(MachineType::AnyTagged(), map));
2772 Goto(&cont);
2773 }
2774 BIND(&cont);
2775}
2776
2777void AccessorAssembler::GenericElementLoad(
2778 TNode<HeapObject> lookup_start_object, TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map,
2779 TNode<Int32T> lookup_start_object_instance_type, TNode<IntPtrT> index,
2780 Label* slow) {
2781 Comment("integer index");
2782
2783 ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
2784
2785 Label if_custom(this), if_element_hole(this), if_oob(this);
2786 Label return_undefined(this);
2787 // Receivers requiring non-standard element accesses (interceptors, access
2788 // checks, strings and string wrappers, proxies) are handled in the runtime.
2789 GotoIf(
2790 IsCustomElementsReceiverInstanceType(lookup_start_object_instance_type),
2791 &if_custom);
2792 TNode<Int32T> elements_kind = LoadMapElementsKind(lookup_start_object_map);
2793 TNode<BoolT> is_jsarray_condition =
2794 IsJSArrayInstanceType(lookup_start_object_instance_type);
2795 TVARIABLE(Float64T, var_double_value);
2796 Label rebox_double(this, &var_double_value);
2797
2798 // Unimplemented elements kinds fall back to a runtime call.
2799 Label* unimplemented_elements_kind = slow;
2800 EmitElementLoad(lookup_start_object, elements_kind, index,
2801 is_jsarray_condition, &if_element_hole, &rebox_double,
2802 &var_double_value, unimplemented_elements_kind, &if_oob, slow,
2803 &direct_exit);
2804
2805 BIND(&rebox_double);
2806 Return(AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(var_double_value.value()));
2807
2808 BIND(&if_oob);
2809 {
2810 Comment("out of bounds");
2811 // On TypedArrays, all OOB loads (positive and negative) return undefined
2812 // without ever checking the prototype chain.
2813 GotoIf(IsJSTypedArrayInstanceType(lookup_start_object_instance_type),
2814 &return_undefined);
2815 // Positive OOB indices within elements index range are effectively the same
2816 // as hole loads. Larger keys and negative keys are named loads.
2817 if (Is64()) {
2818 Branch(UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(index,
2819 IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex)),
2820 &if_element_hole, slow);
2821 } else {
2822 Branch(IntPtrLessThan(index, IntPtrConstant(0)), slow, &if_element_hole);
2823 }
2824 }
2825
2826 BIND(&if_element_hole);
2827 {
2828 Comment("found the hole");
2829 BranchIfPrototypesHaveNoElements(lookup_start_object_map, &return_undefined,
2830 slow);
2831 }
2832
2833 BIND(&if_custom);
2834 {
2835 Comment("check if string");
2836 GotoIfNot(IsStringInstanceType(lookup_start_object_instance_type), slow);
2837 Comment("load string character");
2838 TNode<IntPtrT> length = LoadStringLengthAsWord(CAST(lookup_start_object));
2839 GotoIfNot(UintPtrLessThan(index, length), slow);
2840 TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kStringCharAt, NoContextConstant(),
2841 lookup_start_object, index);
2842 }
2843
2844 BIND(&return_undefined);
2845 Return(UndefinedConstant());
2846}
2847
2848void AccessorAssembler::GenericPropertyLoad(
2849 TNode<HeapObject> lookup_start_object, TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map,
2850 TNode<Int32T> lookup_start_object_instance_type, const LoadICParameters* p,
2851 Label* slow, UseStubCache use_stub_cache) {
2852 DCHECK_EQ(lookup_start_object, p->lookup_start_object());
2853 ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
2854
2855 Comment("key is unique name");
2856 Label if_found_on_lookup_start_object(this), if_property_dictionary(this),
2857 lookup_prototype_chain(this), special_receiver(this);
2858 TVARIABLE(Uint32T, var_details);
2859 TVARIABLE(Object, var_value);
2860
2861 TNode<Name> name = CAST(p->name());
2862
2863 // Receivers requiring non-standard accesses (interceptors, access
2864 // checks, strings and string wrappers) are handled in the runtime.
2865 GotoIf(IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(lookup_start_object_instance_type),
2866 &special_receiver);
2867
2868 // Check if the lookup_start_object has fast or slow properties.
2869 TNode<Uint32T> bitfield3 = LoadMapBitField3(lookup_start_object_map);
2870 GotoIf(IsSetWord32<Map::Bits3::IsDictionaryMapBit>(bitfield3),
2871 &if_property_dictionary);
2872
2873 {
2874 // Try looking up the property on the lookup_start_object; if unsuccessful,
2875 // look for a handler in the stub cache.
2876 TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors =
2877 LoadMapDescriptors(lookup_start_object_map);
2878
2879 Label if_descriptor_found(this), try_stub_cache(this);
2880 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_name_index);
2881 Label* notfound = use_stub_cache == kUseStubCache ? &try_stub_cache
2882 : &lookup_prototype_chain;
2883 DescriptorLookup(name, descriptors, bitfield3, &if_descriptor_found,
2884 &var_name_index, notfound);
2885
2886 BIND(&if_descriptor_found);
2887 {
2888 LoadPropertyFromFastObject(lookup_start_object, lookup_start_object_map,
2889 descriptors, var_name_index.value(),
2890 &var_details, &var_value);
2891 Goto(&if_found_on_lookup_start_object);
2892 }
2893
2894 if (use_stub_cache == kUseStubCache) {
2895 DCHECK_EQ(lookup_start_object, p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object());
2896 Label stub_cache(this);
2897 BIND(&try_stub_cache);
2898 // When there is no feedback vector don't use stub cache.
2899 GotoIfNot(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &stub_cache);
2900 // Fall back to the slow path for private symbols.
2901 Branch(IsPrivateSymbol(name), slow, &lookup_prototype_chain);
2902
2903 BIND(&stub_cache);
2904 Comment("stub cache probe for fast property load");
2905 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
2906 Label found_handler(this, &var_handler), stub_cache_miss(this);
2907 TryProbeStubCache(isolate()->load_stub_cache(), lookup_start_object,
2908 lookup_start_object_map, name, &found_handler,
2909 &var_handler, &stub_cache_miss);
2910 BIND(&found_handler);
2911 {
2912 LazyLoadICParameters lazy_p(p);
2913 HandleLoadICHandlerCase(&lazy_p, var_handler.value(), &stub_cache_miss,
2914 &direct_exit);
2915 }
2916
2917 BIND(&stub_cache_miss);
2918 {
2919 // TODO(jkummerow): Check if the property exists on the prototype
2920 // chain. If it doesn't, then there's no point in missing.
2921 Comment("KeyedLoadGeneric_miss");
2922 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kKeyedLoadIC_Miss, p->context(),
2923 p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object(), name, p->slot(),
2924 p->vector());
2925 }
2926 }
2927 }
2928
2929 BIND(&if_property_dictionary);
2930 {
2931 Comment("dictionary property load");
2932 // We checked for LAST_CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_RECEIVER before, which rules out
2933 // seeing global objects here (which would need special handling).
2934
2935 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_name_index);
2936 Label dictionary_found(this, &var_name_index);
2937 TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties =
2938 CAST(LoadSlowProperties(CAST(lookup_start_object)));
2939 NameDictionaryLookup<PropertyDictionary>(properties, name,
2940 &dictionary_found, &var_name_index,
2941 &lookup_prototype_chain);
2942 BIND(&dictionary_found);
2943 {
2944 LoadPropertyFromDictionary<PropertyDictionary>(
2945 properties, var_name_index.value(), &var_details, &var_value);
2946 Goto(&if_found_on_lookup_start_object);
2947 }
2948 }
2949
2950 BIND(&if_found_on_lookup_start_object);
2951 {
2952 TNode<Object> value = CallGetterIfAccessor(
2953 var_value.value(), lookup_start_object, var_details.value(),
2954 p->context(), p->receiver(), p->name(), slow);
2955 Return(value);
2956 }
2957
2958 BIND(&lookup_prototype_chain);
2959 {
2960 TVARIABLE(Map, var_holder_map);
2961 TVARIABLE(Int32T, var_holder_instance_type);
2962 Label return_undefined(this), is_private_symbol(this);
2963 Label loop(this, {&var_holder_map, &var_holder_instance_type});
2964
2965 var_holder_map = lookup_start_object_map;
2966 var_holder_instance_type = lookup_start_object_instance_type;
2967 GotoIf(IsPrivateSymbol(name), &is_private_symbol);
2968
2969 Goto(&loop);
2970 BIND(&loop);
2971 {
2972 // Bailout if it can be an integer indexed exotic case.
2973 GotoIf(InstanceTypeEqual(var_holder_instance_type.value(),
2974 JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE),
2975 slow);
2976 TNode<HeapObject> proto = LoadMapPrototype(var_holder_map.value());
2977 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(proto, NullConstant()), &return_undefined);
2978 TNode<Map> proto_map = LoadMap(proto);
2979 TNode<Uint16T> proto_instance_type = LoadMapInstanceType(proto_map);
2980 var_holder_map = proto_map;
2981 var_holder_instance_type = proto_instance_type;
2982 Label next_proto(this), return_value(this, &var_value), goto_slow(this);
2983 TryGetOwnProperty(p->context(), p->receiver(), CAST(proto), proto_map,
2984 proto_instance_type, name, &return_value, &var_value,
2985 &next_proto, &goto_slow);
2986
2987 // This trampoline and the next are required to appease Turbofan's
2988 // variable merging.
2989 BIND(&next_proto);
2990 Goto(&loop);
2991
2992 BIND(&goto_slow);
2993 Goto(slow);
2994
2995 BIND(&return_value);
2996 Return(var_value.value());
2997 }
2998
2999 BIND(&is_private_symbol);
3000 {
3001 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsPrivateSymbol(name));
3002
3003 // For private names that don't exist on the receiver, we bail
3004 // to the runtime to throw. For private symbols, we just return
3005 // undefined.
3006 Branch(IsPrivateName(CAST(name)), slow, &return_undefined);
3007 }
3008
3009 BIND(&return_undefined);
3010 Return(UndefinedConstant());
3011 }
3012
3013 BIND(&special_receiver);
3014 {
3015 // TODO(ishell): Consider supporting WasmObjects.
3016 // TODO(jkummerow): Consider supporting JSModuleNamespace.
3017 GotoIfNot(
3018 InstanceTypeEqual(lookup_start_object_instance_type, JS_PROXY_TYPE),
3019 slow);
3020
3021 // Private field/symbol lookup is not supported.
3022 GotoIf(IsPrivateSymbol(name), slow);
3023
3024 direct_exit.ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kProxyGetProperty, p->context(),
3025 lookup_start_object, name, p->receiver(),
3026 SmiConstant(OnNonExistent::kReturnUndefined));
3027 }
3028}
3029
3031
3032enum AccessorAssembler::StubCacheTable : int {
3033 kPrimary = static_cast<int>(StubCache::kPrimary),
3034 kSecondary = static_cast<int>(StubCache::kSecondary)
3035};
3036
3037TNode<IntPtrT> AccessorAssembler::StubCachePrimaryOffset(TNode<Name> name,
3038 TNode<Map> map) {
3039 // Compute the hash of the name (use entire hash field).
3040 TNode<Uint32T> raw_hash_field = LoadNameRawHash(name);
3041 CSA_DCHECK(this,
3042 Word32Equal(Word32And(raw_hash_field,
3043 Int32Constant(Name::kHashNotComputedMask)),
3044 Int32Constant(0)));
3045
3046 // Using only the low bits in 64-bit mode is unlikely to increase the
3047 // risk of collision even if the heap is spread over an area larger than
3048 // 4Gb (and not at all if it isn't).
3049 TNode<IntPtrT> map_word = BitcastTaggedToWord(map);
3050
3051 TNode<Int32T> map32 = TruncateIntPtrToInt32(UncheckedCast<IntPtrT>(
3052 WordXor(map_word, WordShr(map_word, StubCache::kPrimaryTableBits))));
3053 // Base the offset on a simple combination of name and map.
3054 TNode<Word32T> hash = Int32Add(raw_hash_field, map32);
3055 uint32_t mask = (StubCache::kPrimaryTableSize - 1)
3056 << StubCache::kCacheIndexShift;
3057 TNode<UintPtrT> result =
3058 ChangeUint32ToWord(Word32And(hash, Int32Constant(mask)));
3059 return Signed(result);
3060}
3061
3062TNode<IntPtrT> AccessorAssembler::StubCacheSecondaryOffset(TNode<Name> name,
3063 TNode<Map> map) {
3064 // See v8::internal::StubCache::SecondaryOffset().
3065
3066 // Use the seed from the primary cache in the secondary cache.
3067 TNode<Int32T> name32 = TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWord(name));
3068 TNode<Int32T> map32 = TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWord(map));
3069 // Base the offset on a simple combination of name and map.
3070 TNode<Word32T> hash_a = Int32Add(map32, name32);
3071 TNode<Word32T> hash_b = Word32Shr(hash_a, StubCache::kSecondaryTableBits);
3072 TNode<Word32T> hash = Int32Add(hash_a, hash_b);
3073 int32_t mask = (StubCache::kSecondaryTableSize - 1)
3074 << StubCache::kCacheIndexShift;
3075 TNode<UintPtrT> result =
3076 ChangeUint32ToWord(Word32And(hash, Int32Constant(mask)));
3077 return Signed(result);
3078}
3079
3080void AccessorAssembler::TryProbeStubCacheTable(
3081 StubCache* stub_cache, StubCacheTable table_id, TNode<IntPtrT> entry_offset,
3082 TNode<Object> name, TNode<Map> map, Label* if_handler,
3083 TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_handler, Label* if_miss) {
3084 StubCache::Table table = static_cast<StubCache::Table>(table_id);
3085 // The {table_offset} holds the entry offset times four (due to masking
3086 // and shifting optimizations).
3087 const int kMultiplier =
3088 sizeof(StubCache::Entry) >> StubCache::kCacheIndexShift;
3089 entry_offset = IntPtrMul(entry_offset, IntPtrConstant(kMultiplier));
3090
3091 TNode<ExternalReference> key_base = ExternalConstant(
3092 ExternalReference::Create(stub_cache->key_reference(table)));
3093
3094 // Check that the key in the entry matches the name.
3095 DCHECK_EQ(0, offsetof(StubCache::Entry, key));
3096 TNode<HeapObject> cached_key =
3097 CAST(Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), key_base, entry_offset));
3098 GotoIf(TaggedNotEqual(name, cached_key), if_miss);
3099
3100 // Check that the map in the entry matches.
3101 TNode<Object> cached_map = Load<Object>(
3102 key_base,
3103 IntPtrAdd(entry_offset, IntPtrConstant(offsetof(StubCache::Entry, map))));
3104 GotoIf(TaggedNotEqual(map, cached_map), if_miss);
3105
3106 TNode<MaybeObject> handler = ReinterpretCast<MaybeObject>(
3107 Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), key_base,
3108 IntPtrAdd(entry_offset,
3109 IntPtrConstant(offsetof(StubCache::Entry, value)))));
3110
3111 // We found the handler.
3112 *var_handler = handler;
3113 Goto(if_handler);
3114}
3115
3116void AccessorAssembler::TryProbeStubCache(StubCache* stub_cache,
3117 TNode<Object> lookup_start_object,
3118 TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map,
3119 TNode<Name> name, Label* if_handler,
3120 TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_handler,
3121 Label* if_miss) {
3122 Label try_secondary(this), miss(this);
3123
3124 Counters* counters = isolate()->counters();
3125 IncrementCounter(counters->megamorphic_stub_cache_probes(), 1);
3126
3127 // Probe the primary table.
3128 TNode<IntPtrT> primary_offset =
3129 StubCachePrimaryOffset(name, lookup_start_object_map);
3130 TryProbeStubCacheTable(stub_cache, kPrimary, primary_offset, name,
3131 lookup_start_object_map, if_handler, var_handler,
3132 &try_secondary);
3133
3134 BIND(&try_secondary);
3135 {
3136 // Probe the secondary table.
3137 TNode<IntPtrT> secondary_offset =
3138 StubCacheSecondaryOffset(name, lookup_start_object_map);
3139 TryProbeStubCacheTable(stub_cache, kSecondary, secondary_offset, name,
3140 lookup_start_object_map, if_handler, var_handler,
3141 &miss);
3142 }
3143
3144 BIND(&miss);
3145 {
3146 IncrementCounter(counters->megamorphic_stub_cache_misses(), 1);
3147 Goto(if_miss);
3148 }
3149}

3152
3153void AccessorAssembler::LoadIC_BytecodeHandler(const LazyLoadICParameters* p,
3154 ExitPoint* exit_point) {
3155 // Must be kept in sync with LoadIC.
3156
3157 // This function is hand-tuned to omit frame construction for common cases,
3158 // e.g.: monomorphic field and constant loads through smi handlers.
3159 // Polymorphic ICs with a hit in the first two entries also omit frames.
3160 // TODO(jgruber): Frame omission is fragile and can be affected by minor
3161 // changes in control flow and logic. We currently have no way of ensuring
3162 // that no frame is constructed, so it's easy to break this optimization by
3163 // accident.
3164 Label stub_call(this, Label::kDeferred), miss(this, Label::kDeferred),
3165 no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred);
3166
3167 GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &no_feedback);
3168
3169 TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map =
3170 LoadReceiverMap(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object());
3171
3172 // Inlined fast path.
3173 {
3174 Comment("LoadIC_BytecodeHandler_fast");
3175
3176 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
3177 Label try_polymorphic(this), if_handler(this, &var_handler);
3178
3179 TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_lookup_start_object_map =
3180 MakeWeak(lookup_start_object_map);
3181 TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback = TryMonomorphicCase(
3182 p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_lookup_start_object_map, &if_handler,
3183 &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
3184
3185 BIND(&if_handler);
3186 HandleLoadICHandlerCase(p, var_handler.value(), &miss, exit_point);
3187
3188 BIND(&try_polymorphic);
3189 {
3190 TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback =
3191 GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
3192 GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)), &stub_call);
3193 HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_lookup_start_object_map, CAST(strong_feedback),
3194 &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
3195 }
3196 }
3197
3198 BIND(&stub_call);
3199 {
3200 Comment("LoadIC_BytecodeHandler_noninlined");
3201
3202 // Call into the stub that implements the non-inlined parts of LoadIC.
3203 exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kLoadIC_Noninlined, p->context(),
3204 p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object(),
3205 p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
3206 }
3207
3208 BIND(&no_feedback);
3209 {
3210 Comment("LoadIC_BytecodeHandler_nofeedback");
3211 // Call into the stub that implements the non-inlined parts of LoadIC.
3212 exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kLoadIC_NoFeedback, p->context(),
3213 p->receiver(), p->name(),
3214 SmiConstant(FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadProperty));
3215 }
3216
3217 BIND(&miss);
3218 {
3219 Comment("LoadIC_BytecodeHandler_miss");
3220
3221 exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadIC_Miss, p->context(),
3222 p->receiver(), p->name(), p->slot(),
3223 p->vector());
3224 }
3225}
3226
3227void AccessorAssembler::LoadIC(const LoadICParameters* p) {
3228 // Must be kept in sync with LoadIC_BytecodeHandler.
3229
3230 ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
3231
3232 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
3233 Label if_handler(this, &var_handler), non_inlined(this, Label::kDeferred),
3234 try_polymorphic(this), miss(this, Label::kDeferred),
3235 no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred);
3236
3237 TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map =
3238 LoadReceiverMap(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object());
3239
3240 GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &no_feedback);
3241
3242 // Check monomorphic case.
3243 TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_lookup_start_object_map =
3244 MakeWeak(lookup_start_object_map);
3245 TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback = TryMonomorphicCase(
3246 p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_lookup_start_object_map, &if_handler,
3247 &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
3248 BIND(&if_handler);
3249 {
3250 LazyLoadICParameters lazy_p(p);
3251 HandleLoadICHandlerCase(&lazy_p, var_handler.value(), &miss, &direct_exit);
3252 }
3253
3254 BIND(&try_polymorphic);
3255 TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
3256 {
3257 // Check polymorphic case.
3258 Comment("LoadIC_try_polymorphic");
3259 GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)), &non_inlined);
3260 HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_lookup_start_object_map, CAST(strong_feedback),
3261 &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
3262 }
3263
3264 BIND(&non_inlined);
3265 {
3266 LoadIC_Noninlined(p, lookup_start_object_map, strong_feedback, &var_handler,
3267 &if_handler, &miss, &direct_exit);
3268 }
3269
3270 BIND(&no_feedback);
3271 {
3272 Comment("LoadIC_nofeedback");
3273 // Call into the stub that implements the non-inlined parts of LoadIC.
3274 direct_exit.ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kLoadIC_NoFeedback, p->context(),
3275 p->receiver(), p->name(),
3276 SmiConstant(FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadProperty));
3277 }
3278
3279 BIND(&miss);
3280 direct_exit.ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadIC_Miss, p->context(),
3281 p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object(),
3282 p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
3283}
3284
3285void AccessorAssembler::LoadSuperIC(const LoadICParameters* p) {
3286 ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
3287
3288 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
3289 Label if_handler(this, &var_handler), no_feedback(this),
3290 non_inlined(this, Label::kDeferred), try_polymorphic(this),
3291 miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
3292
3293 GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &no_feedback);
3294
3295 // The lookup start object cannot be a SMI, since it's the home object's
3296 // prototype, and it's not possible to set SMIs as prototypes.
3297 TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map = LoadMap(CAST(p->lookup_start_object()));
3298 GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(lookup_start_object_map), &miss);
3299
3300 TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_lookup_start_object_map =
3301 MakeWeak(lookup_start_object_map);
3302 TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback = TryMonomorphicCase(
3303 p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_lookup_start_object_map, &if_handler,
3304 &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
3305
3306 BIND(&if_handler);
3307 {
3308 LazyLoadICParameters lazy_p(p);
3309 HandleLoadICHandlerCase(&lazy_p, var_handler.value(), &miss, &direct_exit);
3310 }
3311
3312 BIND(&no_feedback);
3313 { LoadSuperIC_NoFeedback(p); }
3314
3315 BIND(&try_polymorphic);
3316 TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
3317 {
3318 Comment("LoadSuperIC_try_polymorphic");
3319 GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)), &non_inlined);
3320 HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_lookup_start_object_map, CAST(strong_feedback),
3321 &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
3322 }
3323
3324 BIND(&non_inlined);
3325 {
3326 // LoadIC_Noninlined can be used here, since it handles the
3327 // lookup_start_object != receiver case gracefully.
3328 LoadIC_Noninlined(p, lookup_start_object_map, strong_feedback, &var_handler,
3329 &if_handler, &miss, &direct_exit);
3330 }
3331
3332 BIND(&miss);
3333 direct_exit.ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadWithReceiverIC_Miss, p->context(),
3334 p->receiver(), p->lookup_start_object(),
3335 p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
3336}
3337
3338void AccessorAssembler::LoadIC_Noninlined(const LoadICParameters* p,
3339 TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map,
3340 TNode<HeapObject> feedback,
3341 TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_handler,
3342 Label* if_handler, Label* miss,
3343 ExitPoint* exit_point) {
3344 // Not monomorphic -- this cases is handled in the bytecode handler.
3345 CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedNotEqual(lookup_start_object_map, feedback));
3346 CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32BinaryNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(feedback))));
3347 DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, var_handler->rep());
3348
3349 {
3350 Label try_megamorphic(this), try_megadom(this);
3351 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant()),
3352 &try_megamorphic);
3353 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(feedback, MegaDOMSymbolConstant()), &try_megadom);
3354 Goto(miss);
3355
3356 BIND(&try_megamorphic);
3357 {
3358 TryProbeStubCache(isolate()->load_stub_cache(), p->lookup_start_object(),
3359 lookup_start_object_map, CAST(p->name()), if_handler,
3360 var_handler, miss);
3361 }
3362
3363 BIND(&try_megadom);
3364 {
3365 TryMegaDOMCase(p->lookup_start_object(), lookup_start_object_map,
3366 var_handler, p->vector(), p->slot(), miss, exit_point);
3367 }
3368 }
3369}

3371void AccessorAssembler::LoadIC_NoFeedback(const LoadICParameters* p,
3372 TNode<Smi> ic_kind) {
3373 Label miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
3374 TNode<Object> lookup_start_object = p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object();
3375 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(lookup_start_object), &miss);
3376 TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map = LoadMap(CAST(lookup_start_object));
3377 GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(lookup_start_object_map), &miss);
3378
3379 TNode<Uint16T> instance_type = LoadMapInstanceType(lookup_start_object_map);
3380
3381 {
3382 // Special case for Function.prototype load, because it's very common
3383 // for ICs that are only executed once (MyFunc.prototype.foo = ...).
3384 Label not_function_prototype(this, Label::kDeferred);
3385 GotoIfNot(IsJSFunctionInstanceType(instance_type), &not_function_prototype);
3386 GotoIfNot(IsPrototypeString(p->name()), &not_function_prototype);
3387
3388 GotoIfPrototypeRequiresRuntimeLookup(CAST(lookup_start_object),
3389 lookup_start_object_map,
3390 &not_function_prototype);
3391 Return(LoadJSFunctionPrototype(CAST(lookup_start_object), &miss));
3392 BIND(&not_function_prototype);
3393 }
3394
3395 GenericPropertyLoad(CAST(lookup_start_object), lookup_start_object_map,
3396 instance_type, p, &miss, kDontUseStubCache);
3397
3398 BIND(&miss);
3399 {
3400 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadNoFeedbackIC_Miss, p->context(),
3401 p->receiver(), p->name(), ic_kind);
3402 }
3403}

3405void AccessorAssembler::LoadSuperIC_NoFeedback(const LoadICParameters* p) {
3406 Label miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
3407 TNode<Object> lookup_start_object = p->lookup_start_object();
3408
3409 // The lookup start object cannot be a SMI, since it's the home object's

3418

3426void AccessorAssembler::LoadGlobalIC(TNode<HeapObject> maybe_feedback_vector,
3427 const LazyNode<TaggedIndex>& lazy_slot,
3428 const LazyNode<Context>& lazy_context,
3429 const LazyNode<Name>& lazy_name,
3430 TypeofMode typeof_mode,
3431 ExitPoint* exit_point) {
3432 Label try_handler(this, Label::kDeferred), miss(this, Label::kDeferred),
3433 no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred);
3434
3435 GotoIf(IsUndefined(maybe_feedback_vector), &no_feedback);
3436 {
3437 TNode<TaggedIndex> slot = lazy_slot();
3438
3439 {
3440 TNode<FeedbackVector> vector = CAST(maybe_feedback_vector);
3441 LoadGlobalIC_TryPropertyCellCase(vector, slot, lazy_context, exit_point,
3442 &try_handler, &miss);
3443
3444 BIND(&try_handler);
3445 LoadGlobalIC_TryHandlerCase(vector, slot, lazy_context, lazy_name,
3446 typeof_mode, exit_point, &miss);
3447 }
3448
3449 BIND(&miss);
3450 {
3451 Comment("LoadGlobalIC_MissCase");
3452 TNode<Context> context = lazy_context();
3453 TNode<Name> name = lazy_name();
3454 exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadGlobalIC_Miss, context, name,
3455 slot, maybe_feedback_vector,
3456 SmiConstant(typeof_mode));
3457 }
3458 }
3459
3460 BIND(&no_feedback);
3461 {
3462 int ic_kind =
3463 static_cast<int>((typeof_mode == TypeofMode::kInside)
3464 ? FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadGlobalInsideTypeof
3465 : FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadGlobalNotInsideTypeof);
3466 exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kLoadGlobalIC_NoFeedback,
3467 lazy_context(), lazy_name(),
3468 SmiConstant(ic_kind));
3469 }
3470}
3471
3472void AccessorAssembler::LoadGlobalIC_TryPropertyCellCase(
3473 TNode<FeedbackVector> vector, TNode<TaggedIndex> slot,
3474 const LazyNode<Context>& lazy_context, ExitPoint* exit_point,
3475 Label* try_handler, Label* miss) {
3476 Comment("LoadGlobalIC_TryPropertyCellCase");
3477
3478 Label if_lexical_var(this), if_property_cell(this);
3479 TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_weak_ref = LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(vector, slot);
3480 Branch(TaggedIsSmi(maybe_weak_ref), &if_lexical_var, &if_property_cell);
3481
3482 BIND(&if_property_cell);
3483 {
3484 // This branch also handles the "handler mode": the weak reference is
3485 // cleared, the feedback extra is the handler. In that case we jump to
3486 // try_handler. (See FeedbackNexus::ConfigureHandlerMode.)
3487 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_weak_ref));
3488 TNode<PropertyCell> property_cell =
3489 CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_weak_ref, try_handler));
3490 TNode<Object> value =
3491 LoadObjectField(property_cell, PropertyCell::kValueOffset);
3492 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(value, PropertyCellHoleConstant()), miss);
3493 exit_point->Return(value);
3494 }
3495
3496 BIND(&if_lexical_var);
3497 {
3498 // This branch handles the "lexical variable mode": the feedback is a SMI
3499 // encoding the variable location. (See
3500 // FeedbackNexus::ConfigureLexicalVarMode.)
3501 Comment("Load lexical variable");
3502 TNode<IntPtrT> lexical_handler = SmiUntag(CAST(maybe_weak_ref));
3503 TNode<IntPtrT> context_index =
3504 Signed(DecodeWord<FeedbackNexus::ContextIndexBits>(lexical_handler));
3505 TNode<IntPtrT> slot_index =
3506 Signed(DecodeWord<FeedbackNexus::SlotIndexBits>(lexical_handler));
3507 TNode<Context> context = lazy_context();
3508 TNode<Context> script_context = LoadScriptContext(context, context_index);
3509 TNode<Object> result = LoadContextElement(script_context, slot_index);
3510 exit_point->Return(result);
3511 }
3512}
3513
3514void AccessorAssembler::LoadGlobalIC_TryHandlerCase(
3515 TNode<FeedbackVector> vector, TNode<TaggedIndex> slot,
3516 const LazyNode<Context>& lazy_context, const LazyNode<Name>& lazy_name,
3517 TypeofMode typeof_mode, ExitPoint* exit_point, Label* miss) {
3518 Comment("LoadGlobalIC_TryHandlerCase");
3519
3520 Label call_handler(this), non_smi(this);
3521
3522 TNode<MaybeObject> feedback_element =
3523 LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(vector, slot, kTaggedSize);
3524 TNode<Object> handler = CAST(feedback_element);
3525 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(handler, UninitializedSymbolConstant()), miss);
3526
3527 OnNonExistent on_nonexistent = typeof_mode == TypeofMode::kNotInside
3528 ? OnNonExistent::kThrowReferenceError
3529 : OnNonExistent::kReturnUndefined;
3530
3531 TNode<Context> context = lazy_context();
3532 TNode<NativeContext> native_context = LoadNativeContext(context);
3533 TNode<JSGlobalProxy> receiver =
3534 CAST(LoadContextElement(native_context, Context::GLOBAL_PROXY_INDEX));
3535 TNode<Object> global =
3536 LoadContextElement(native_context, Context::EXTENSION_INDEX);
3537
3538 LazyLoadICParameters p([=] { return context; }, receiver, lazy_name,
3539 [=] { return slot; }, vector, global);
3540
3541 HandleLoadICHandlerCase(&p, handler, miss, exit_point, ICMode::kGlobalIC,
3542 on_nonexistent);
3543}
3544
3545void AccessorAssembler::ScriptContextTableLookup(
3546 TNode<Name> name, TNode<NativeContext> native_context, Label* found_hole,
3547 Label* not_found) {
3548 TNode<ScriptContextTable> script_context_table = CAST(
3549 LoadContextElement(native_context, Context::SCRIPT_CONTEXT_TABLE_INDEX));
3550 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, context_index, IntPtrConstant(-1));
3551 Label loop(this, &context_index);
3552 TNode<IntPtrT> num_script_contexts = PositiveSmiUntag(CAST(LoadObjectField(
3553 script_context_table, offsetof(ScriptContextTable, length_))));
3554 Goto(&loop);
3555
3556 BIND(&loop);
3557 {
3558 context_index = IntPtrAdd(context_index.value(), IntPtrConstant(1));
3559 GotoIf(IntPtrGreaterThanOrEqual(context_index.value(), num_script_contexts),
3560 not_found);
3561
3562 TNode<Context> script_context =
3563 LoadArrayElement(script_context_table, context_index.value());
3564 TNode<ScopeInfo> scope_info =
3565 CAST(LoadContextElement(script_context, Context::SCOPE_INFO_INDEX));
3566
3567 TNode<IntPtrT> context_local_index =
3568 IndexOfLocalName(scope_info, name, &loop);
3569
3570 TNode<IntPtrT> var_index =
3571 IntPtrAdd(IntPtrConstant(Context::MIN_CONTEXT_EXTENDED_SLOTS),
3572 context_local_index);
3573 TNode<Object> result = LoadContextElement(script_context, var_index);
3574 GotoIf(IsTheHole(result), found_hole);
3575 Return(result);
3576 }
3577}
3578
3579void AccessorAssembler::LoadGlobalIC_NoFeedback(TNode<Context> context,
3580 TNode<Object> name,
3581 TNode<Smi> smi_typeof_mode) {
3582 TNode<NativeContext> native_context = LoadNativeContext(context);
3583 Label regular_load(this), throw_reference_error(this, Label::kDeferred);
3584
3585 GotoIfNot(IsString(CAST(name)), &regular_load);
3586 ScriptContextTableLookup(CAST(name), native_context, &throw_reference_error,
3587 &regular_load);
3588
3589 BIND(&throw_reference_error);
3590 Return(CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowReferenceError, context, name));
3591
3592 BIND(&regular_load);
3593 TNode<JSGlobalObject> global_object =
3594 CAST(LoadContextElement(native_context, Context::EXTENSION_INDEX));
3595 TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kLoadIC_NoFeedback, context, global_object, name,
3596 smi_typeof_mode);
3597}
3598
3599void AccessorAssembler::KeyedLoadIC(const LoadICParameters* p,
3600 LoadAccessMode access_mode) {
3601 ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
3602
3603 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
3604 Label if_handler(this, &var_handler), try_polymorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
3605 try_megamorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
3606 try_uninitialized(this, Label::kDeferred),
3607 try_polymorphic_name(this, Label::kDeferred),
3608 miss(this, Label::kDeferred), generic(this, Label::kDeferred);
3609
3610 TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map =
3611 LoadReceiverMap(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object());
3612 GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(lookup_start_object_map), &miss);
3613
3614 TryEnumeratedKeyedLoad(p, lookup_start_object_map, &direct_exit);
3615
3616 GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &generic);
3617
3618 // Check monomorphic case.
3619 TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_lookup_start_object_map =
3620 MakeWeak(lookup_start_object_map);
3621 TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback = TryMonomorphicCase(
3622 p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_lookup_start_object_map, &if_handler,
3623 &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
3624 BIND(&if_handler);
3625 {
3626 LazyLoadICParameters lazy_p(p);
3627 HandleLoadICHandlerCase(
3628 &lazy_p, var_handler.value(), &miss, &direct_exit, ICMode::kNonGlobalIC,
3629 OnNonExistent::kReturnUndefined, kSupportElements, access_mode);
3630 }
3631
3632 BIND(&try_polymorphic);
3633 TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
3634 {
3635 // Check polymorphic case.
3636 Comment("KeyedLoadIC_try_polymorphic");
3637 GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)), &try_megamorphic);
3638 HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_lookup_start_object_map, CAST(strong_feedback),
3639 &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
3640 }
3641
3642 BIND(&try_megamorphic);
3643 {
3644 // Check megamorphic case.
3645 Comment("KeyedLoadIC_try_megamorphic");
3646 Branch(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant()), &generic,
3647 &try_uninitialized);
3648 }
3649
3650 BIND(&generic);
3651 {
3652 // TODO(jkummerow): Inline this? Or some of it?
3653 TailCallBuiltin(
3654 access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kLoad ? Builtin::kKeyedLoadIC_Megamorphic
3655 : Builtin::kKeyedHasIC_Megamorphic,
3656 p->context(), p->receiver(), p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
3657 }
3658
3659 BIND(&try_uninitialized);
3660 {
3661 // Check uninitialized case.
3662 Comment("KeyedLoadIC_try_uninitialized");
3663 Branch(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, UninitializedSymbolConstant()), &miss,
3664 &try_polymorphic_name);
3665 }
3666
3667 BIND(&try_polymorphic_name);
3668 {
3669 // We might have a name in feedback, and a weak fixed array in the next
3670 // slot.
3671 Comment("KeyedLoadIC_try_polymorphic_name");
3672 TVARIABLE(Name, var_name);
3673 Label if_polymorphic_name(this), feedback_matches(this),
3674 if_internalized(this), if_notinternalized(this, Label::kDeferred);
3675
3676 // Fast-case: The recorded {feedback} matches the {name}.
3677 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, p->name()), &feedback_matches);
3678
3679 {
3680 // Try to internalize the {name} if it isn't already.
3681 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_index);
3682 TryToName(p->name(), &miss, &var_index, &if_internalized, &var_name,
3683 &miss, &if_notinternalized);
3684 }
3685
3686 BIND(&if_internalized);
3687 {
3688 // The {var_name} now contains a unique name.
3689 Branch(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, var_name.value()),
3690 &if_polymorphic_name, &miss);
3691 }
3692
3693 BIND(&if_notinternalized);
3694 {
3695 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_index);
3696 TryInternalizeString(CAST(p->name()), &miss, &var_index, &if_internalized,
3697 &var_name, &miss, &miss);
3698 }
3699
3700 BIND(&feedback_matches);
3701 {
3702 var_name = CAST(p->name());
3703 Goto(&if_polymorphic_name);
3704 }
3705
3706 BIND(&if_polymorphic_name);
3707 {
3708 // If the name comparison succeeded, we know we have a weak fixed array
3709 // with at least one map/handler pair.
3710 TailCallBuiltin(access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kLoad
3711 ? Builtin::kKeyedLoadIC_PolymorphicName
3712 : Builtin::kKeyedHasIC_PolymorphicName,
3713 p->context(), p->receiver(), var_name.value(), p->slot(),
3714 p->vector());
3715 }
3716 }
3717
3718 BIND(&miss);
3719 {
3720 Comment("KeyedLoadIC_miss");
3721 TailCallRuntime(
3722 access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kLoad ? Runtime::kKeyedLoadIC_Miss
3723 : Runtime::kKeyedHasIC_Miss,
3724 p->context(), p->receiver(), p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
3725 }
3726}
3727
3728void AccessorAssembler::KeyedLoadICGeneric(const LoadICParameters* p) {
3729 TVARIABLE(Object, var_name, p->name());
3730
3731 Label if_runtime(this, Label::kDeferred);
3732 TNode<Object> lookup_start_object = p->lookup_start_object();
3733 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(lookup_start_object), &if_runtime);
3734 GotoIf(IsNullOrUndefined(lookup_start_object), &if_runtime);
3735
3736 {
3737 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_index);
3738 TVARIABLE(Name, var_unique);
3739 Label if_index(this), if_unique_name(this, &var_name), if_notunique(this),
3740 if_other(this, Label::kDeferred);
3741
3742 TryToName(var_name.value(), &if_index, &var_index, &if_unique_name,
3743 &var_unique, &if_other, &if_notunique);
3744
3745 BIND(&if_unique_name);
3746 {
3747 LoadICParameters pp(p, var_unique.value());
3748 TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map = LoadMap(CAST(lookup_start_object));
3749 GenericPropertyLoad(CAST(lookup_start_object), lookup_start_object_map,
3750 LoadMapInstanceType(lookup_start_object_map), &pp,
3751 &if_runtime);
3752 }
3753
3754 BIND(&if_other);
3755 {
3756 var_name = CallBuiltin(Builtin::kToName, p->context(), var_name.value());
3757 TryToName(var_name.value(), &if_index, &var_index, &if_unique_name,
3758 &var_unique, &if_runtime, &if_notunique);
3759 }
3760
3761 BIND(&if_notunique);
3762 {
3763 if (v8_flags.internalize_on_the_fly) {
3764 // Ideally we could return undefined directly here if the name is not
3765 // found in the string table, i.e. it was never internalized, but that
3766 // invariant doesn't hold with named property interceptors (at this
3767 // point), so we take the {if_runtime} path instead.
3768 Label if_in_string_table(this);
3769 TryInternalizeString(CAST(var_name.value()), &if_index, &var_index,
3770 &if_in_string_table, &var_unique, &if_runtime,
3771 &if_runtime);
3772
3773 BIND(&if_in_string_table);
3774 {
3775 // TODO(bmeurer): We currently use a version of GenericPropertyLoad
3776 // here, where we don't try to probe the megamorphic stub cache
3777 // after successfully internalizing the incoming string. Past
3778 // experiments with this have shown that it causes too much traffic
3779 // on the stub cache. We may want to re-evaluate that in the future.
3780 LoadICParameters pp(p, var_unique.value());
3781 TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map =
3782 LoadMap(CAST(lookup_start_object));
3783 GenericPropertyLoad(CAST(lookup_start_object),
3784 lookup_start_object_map,
3785 LoadMapInstanceType(lookup_start_object_map), &pp,
3786 &if_runtime, kDontUseStubCache);
3787 }
3788 } else {
3789 Goto(&if_runtime);
3790 }
3791 }
3792
3793 BIND(&if_index);
3794 {
3795 TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map = LoadMap(CAST(lookup_start_object));
3796 GenericElementLoad(CAST(lookup_start_object), lookup_start_object_map,
3797 LoadMapInstanceType(lookup_start_object_map),
3798 var_index.value(), &if_runtime);
3799 }
3800 }
3801
3802 BIND(&if_runtime);
3803 {
3804 Comment("KeyedLoadGeneric_slow");
3805 // TODO(jkummerow): Should we use the GetProperty TF stub instead?
3806 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kGetProperty, p->context(),
3807 p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object(), var_name.value());
3808 }
3809}
3810
3811void AccessorAssembler::KeyedLoadICPolymorphicName(const LoadICParameters* p,
3812 LoadAccessMode access_mode) {
3813 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
3814 Label if_handler(this, &var_handler), miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
3815
3816 TNode<Object> lookup_start_object = p->lookup_start_object();
3817 TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map = LoadReceiverMap(lookup_start_object);
3818 TNode<Name> name = CAST(p->name());
3819 TNode<FeedbackVector> vector = CAST(p->vector());
3820 TNode<TaggedIndex> slot = p->slot();
3821 TNode<Context> context = p->context();
3822
3823 // When we get here, we know that the {name} matches the recorded
3824 // feedback name in the {vector} and can safely be used for the
3825 // LoadIC handler logic below.
3826 CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32BinaryNot(IsDeprecatedMap(lookup_start_object_map)));
3827 CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedEqual(name, LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(vector, slot)),
3828 name, vector);
3829
3830 // Check if we have a matching handler for the {lookup_start_object_map}.
3831 TNode<MaybeObject> feedback_element =
3832 LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(vector, slot, kTaggedSize);
3833 TNode<WeakFixedArray> array = CAST(feedback_element);
3834 HandlePolymorphicCase(MakeWeak(lookup_start_object_map), array, &if_handler,
3835 &var_handler, &miss);
3836
3837 BIND(&if_handler);
3838 {
3839 ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
3840 LazyLoadICParameters lazy_p(p);
3841 HandleLoadICHandlerCase(
3842 &lazy_p, var_handler.value(), &miss, &direct_exit, ICMode::kNonGlobalIC,
3843 OnNonExistent::kReturnUndefined, kOnlyProperties, access_mode);
3844 }
3845
3846 BIND(&miss);
3847 {
3848 Comment("KeyedLoadIC_miss");
3849 TailCallRuntime(
3850 access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kLoad ? Runtime::kKeyedLoadIC_Miss
3851 : Runtime::kKeyedHasIC_Miss,
3852 context, p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object(), name, slot, vector);
3853 }
3854}
3855
3856void AccessorAssembler::StoreIC(const StoreICParameters* p) {
3857 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler,
3858 ReinterpretCast<MaybeObject>(SmiConstant(0)));
3859
3860 Label if_handler(this, &var_handler),
3861 if_handler_from_stub_cache(this, &var_handler, Label::kDeferred),
3862 try_polymorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
3863 try_megamorphic(this, Label::kDeferred), miss(this, Label::kDeferred),
3864 no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred);
3865
3866 TNode<Map> receiver_map = LoadReceiverMap(p->receiver());
3867 GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(receiver_map), &miss);
3868
3869 GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &no_feedback);
3870
3871 // Check monomorphic case.
3872 TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_receiver_map = MakeWeak(receiver_map);
3873 TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback =
3874 TryMonomorphicCase(p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_receiver_map,
3875 &if_handler, &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
3876 BIND(&if_handler);
3877 {
3878 Comment("StoreIC_if_handler");
3879 HandleStoreICHandlerCase(p, var_handler.value(), &miss,
3880 ICMode::kNonGlobalIC);
3881 }
3882
3883 BIND(&try_polymorphic);
3884 TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
3885 {
3886 // Check polymorphic case.
3887 Comment("StoreIC_try_polymorphic");
3888 GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)), &try_megamorphic);
3889 HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_receiver_map, CAST(strong_feedback), &if_handler,
3890 &var_handler, &miss);
3891 }
3892
3893 BIND(&try_megamorphic);
3894 {
3895 // Check megamorphic case.
3896 GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant()), &miss);
3897
3898 TryProbeStubCache(p->stub_cache(isolate()), p->receiver(), receiver_map,
3899 CAST(p->name()), &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
3900 }
3901
3902 BIND(&no_feedback);
3903 {
3904 // TODO(v8:12548): refactor SetNamedIC as a subclass of StoreIC, which can
3905 // be called here and below when !p->IsDefineNamedOwn().
3906 auto builtin = p->IsDefineNamedOwn() ? Builtin::kDefineNamedOwnIC_NoFeedback
3907 : Builtin::kStoreIC_NoFeedback;
3908 TailCallBuiltin(builtin, p->context(), p->receiver(), p->name(),
3909 p->value());
3910 }
3911
3912 BIND(&miss);
3913 {
3914 auto runtime = p->IsDefineNamedOwn() ? Runtime::kDefineNamedOwnIC_Miss
3915 : Runtime::kStoreIC_Miss;
3916 TailCallRuntime(runtime, p->context(), p->value(), p->slot(), p->vector(),
3917 p->receiver(), p->name());
3918 }
3919}
3920
3921void AccessorAssembler::StoreGlobalIC(const StoreICParameters* pp) {
3922 Label no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred), if_lexical_var(this),
3923 if_heapobject(this);
3924 GotoIf(IsUndefined(pp->vector()), &no_feedback);
3925
3926 TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_weak_ref =
3927 LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(pp->vector()), pp->slot());
3928 Branch(TaggedIsSmi(maybe_weak_ref), &if_lexical_var, &if_heapobject);
3929
3930 BIND(&if_heapobject);
3931 {
3932 Label try_handler(this), miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
3933
3934 // This branch also handles the "handler mode": the weak reference is
3935 // cleared, the feedback extra is the handler. In that case we jump to
3936 // try_handler. (See FeedbackNexus::ConfigureHandlerMode.)
3937 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_weak_ref));
3938 TNode<PropertyCell> property_cell =
3939 CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_weak_ref, &try_handler));
3940
3941 ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
3942 StoreGlobalIC_PropertyCellCase(property_cell, pp->value(), &direct_exit,
3943 &miss);
3944
3945 BIND(&try_handler);
3946 {
3947 Comment("StoreGlobalIC_try_handler");
3948 TNode<MaybeObject> handler =
3949 LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(pp->vector()), pp->slot(), kTaggedSize);
3950
3951 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(handler, UninitializedSymbolConstant()), &miss);
3952
3953 DCHECK(pp->receiver_is_null());
3954 DCHECK(pp->flags_is_null());
3955 TNode<NativeContext> native_context = LoadNativeContext(pp->context());
3956 StoreICParameters p(
3957 pp->context(),
3958 LoadContextElement(native_context, Context::GLOBAL_PROXY_INDEX),
3959 pp->name(), pp->value(), std::nullopt, pp->slot(), pp->vector(),
3960 StoreICMode::kDefault);
3961
3962 HandleStoreICHandlerCase(&p, handler, &miss, ICMode::kGlobalIC);
3963 }
3964
3965 BIND(&miss);
3966 {
3967 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreGlobalIC_Miss, pp->context(), pp->value(),
3968 pp->slot(), pp->vector(), pp->name());
3969 }
3970 }
3971
3972 BIND(&if_lexical_var);
3973 {
3974 // This branch handles the "lexical variable mode": the feedback is a SMI
3975 // encoding the variable location. (See
3976 // FeedbackNexus::ConfigureLexicalVarMode.)
3977 Comment("Store lexical variable");
3978 TNode<IntPtrT> lexical_handler = SmiUntag(CAST(maybe_weak_ref));
3979 TNode<IntPtrT> context_index =
3980 Signed(DecodeWord<FeedbackNexus::ContextIndexBits>(lexical_handler));
3981 TNode<IntPtrT> slot_index =
3982 Signed(DecodeWord<FeedbackNexus::SlotIndexBits>(lexical_handler));
3983 TNode<Context> script_context =
3984 LoadScriptContext(pp->context(), context_index);
3985 StoreContextElementAndUpdateSideData(script_context, slot_index,
3986 pp->value());
3987 Return(pp->value());
3988 }
3989
3990 BIND(&no_feedback);
3991 {
3992 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreGlobalICNoFeedback_Miss, pp->context(),
3993 pp->value(), pp->name());
3994 }
3995}
3996
3997void AccessorAssembler::StoreGlobalIC_PropertyCellCase(
3998 TNode<PropertyCell> property_cell, TNode<Object> value,
3999 ExitPoint* exit_point, Label* miss) {
4000 Comment("StoreGlobalIC_TryPropertyCellCase");
4001
4002 // Load the payload of the global parameter cell. A hole indicates that
4003 // the cell has been invalidated and that the store must be handled by the
4004 // runtime.
4005 TNode<Object> cell_contents =
4006 LoadObjectField(property_cell, PropertyCell::kValueOffset);
4007 TNode<Int32T> details = LoadAndUntagToWord32ObjectField(
4008 property_cell, PropertyCell::kPropertyDetailsRawOffset);
4009 GotoIf(IsSetWord32(details, PropertyDetails::kAttributesReadOnlyMask), miss);
4010 CSA_DCHECK(this,
4011 Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::KindField>(details),
4012 Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(PropertyKind::kData))));
4013
4014 TNode<Uint32T> type =
4015 DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::PropertyCellTypeField>(details);
4016
4017 Label constant(this), store(this), not_smi(this);
4018
4019 GotoIf(Word32Equal(type, Int32Constant(
4020 static_cast<int>(PropertyCellType::kConstant))),
4021 &constant);
4022 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsNotAnyHole(cell_contents));
4023
4024 GotoIf(Word32Equal(
4025 type, Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(PropertyCellType::kMutable))),
4026 &store);
4027 CSA_DCHECK(this,
4028 Word32Or(Word32Equal(type, Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(
4029 PropertyCellType::kConstantType))),
4030 Word32Equal(type, Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(
4031 PropertyCellType::kUndefined)))));
4032
4033 GotoIfNot(TaggedIsSmi(cell_contents), &not_smi);
4034 GotoIfNot(TaggedIsSmi(value), miss);
4035 Goto(&store);
4036
4037 BIND(&not_smi);
4038 {
4039 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(value), miss);
4040 TNode<Map> expected_map = LoadMap(CAST(cell_contents));
4041 TNode<Map> map = LoadMap(CAST(value));
4042 GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(expected_map, map), miss);
4043 Goto(&store);
4044 }
4045
4046 BIND(&store);
4047 {
4048 StoreObjectField(property_cell, PropertyCell::kValueOffset, value);
4049 exit_point->Return(value);
4050 }
4051
4052 BIND(&constant);
4053 {
4054 // Since |value| is never the hole, the equality check below also handles an
4055 // invalidated property cell correctly.
4056 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsNotAnyHole(value));
4057 GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(cell_contents, value), miss);
4058 exit_point->Return(value);
4059 }
4060}
4061
4062void AccessorAssembler::KeyedStoreIC(const StoreICParameters* p) {
4063 Label miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
4064 {
4065 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
4066
4067 Label if_handler(this, &var_handler),
4068 try_polymorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
4069 try_megamorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
4070 no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred),
4071 try_polymorphic_name(this, Label::kDeferred);
4072
4073 TNode<Map> receiver_map = LoadReceiverMap(p->receiver());
4074 GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(receiver_map), &miss);
4075
4076 GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &no_feedback);
4077
4078 // Check monomorphic case.
4079 TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_receiver_map = MakeWeak(receiver_map);
4080 TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback =
4081 TryMonomorphicCase(p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_receiver_map,
4082 &if_handler, &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
4083 BIND(&if_handler);
4084 {
4085 Comment("KeyedStoreIC_if_handler");
4086 HandleStoreICHandlerCase(p, var_handler.value(), &miss,
4087 ICMode::kNonGlobalIC, kSupportElements);
4088 }
4089
4090 BIND(&try_polymorphic);
4091 TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
4092 {
4093 // CheckPolymorphic case.
4094 Comment("KeyedStoreIC_try_polymorphic");
4095 GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)),
4096 &try_megamorphic);
4097 HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_receiver_map, CAST(strong_feedback),
4098 &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
4099 }
4100
4101 BIND(&try_megamorphic);
4102 {
4103 // Check megamorphic case.
4104 Comment("KeyedStoreIC_try_megamorphic");
4105 Branch(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant()),
4106 &no_feedback, &try_polymorphic_name);
4107 }
4108
4109 BIND(&no_feedback);
4110 {
4111 TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kKeyedStoreIC_Megamorphic, p->context(),
4112 p->receiver(), p->name(), p->value(), p->slot(),
4113 p->vector());
4114 }
4115
4116 BIND(&try_polymorphic_name);
4117 {
4118 // We might have a name in feedback, and a fixed array in the next slot.
4119 Comment("KeyedStoreIC_try_polymorphic_name");
4120 GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, p->name()), &miss);
4121 // If the name comparison succeeded, we know we have a feedback vector
4122 // with at least one map/handler pair.
4123 TNode<MaybeObject> feedback_element =
4124 LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(p->vector()), p->slot(), kTaggedSize);
4125 TNode<WeakFixedArray> array = CAST(feedback_element);
4126 HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_receiver_map, array, &if_handler, &var_handler,
4127 &miss);
4128 }
4129 }
4130 BIND(&miss);
4131 {
4132 Comment("KeyedStoreIC_miss");
4133 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kKeyedStoreIC_Miss, p->context(), p->value(),
4134 p->slot(), p->vector(), p->receiver(), p->name());
4135 }
4136}
