4138void AccessorAssembler::DefineKeyedOwnIC(const StoreICParameters* p) {
4139 Label miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
4140 {
4141 {
4142 // TODO(v8:13451): Port SetFunctionName to an ic so that we can remove
4143 // the runtime call here. Potentially we may also remove the
4144 // StoreICParameters flags and have builtins:kDefineKeyedOwnIC reusing
4145 // StoreWithVectorDescriptor again.
4146 Label did_set_function_name_if_needed(this);
4147 TNode<Int32T> needs_set_function_name = Word32And(
4148 SmiToInt32(p->flags()),
4149 Int32Constant(
4150 static_cast<int>(DefineKeyedOwnPropertyFlag::kSetFunctionName)));
4151 GotoIfNot(needs_set_function_name, &did_set_function_name_if_needed);
4152
4153 Comment("DefineKeyedOwnIC_set_function_name");
4154 CallRuntime(Runtime::kSetFunctionName, p->context(), p->value(),
4155 p->name());
4156
4157 Goto(&did_set_function_name_if_needed);
4158 BIND(&did_set_function_name_if_needed);
4159 }
4160 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
4161
4162 Label if_handler(this, &var_handler),
4163 try_polymorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
4164 try_megamorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
4165 no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred),
4166 try_polymorphic_name(this, Label::kDeferred);
4167
4168 TNode<Map> receiver_map = LoadReceiverMap(p->receiver());
4169 GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(receiver_map), &miss);
4170
4171 GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &no_feedback);
4172
4173 // Check monomorphic case.
4174 TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_receiver_map = MakeWeak(receiver_map);
4175 TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback =
4176 TryMonomorphicCase(p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_receiver_map,
4177 &if_handler, &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
4178 BIND(&if_handler);
4179 {
4180 Comment("DefineKeyedOwnIC_if_handler");
4181 HandleStoreICHandlerCase(p, var_handler.value(), &miss,
4182 ICMode::kNonGlobalIC, kSupportElements);
4183 }
4184
4185 BIND(&try_polymorphic);
4186 TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
4187 {
4188 // CheckPolymorphic case.
4189 Comment("DefineKeyedOwnIC_try_polymorphic");
4190 GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)),
4191 &try_megamorphic);
4192 HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_receiver_map, CAST(strong_feedback),
4193 &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
4194 }
4195
4196 BIND(&try_megamorphic);
4197 {
4198 // Check megamorphic case.
4199 Comment("DefineKeyedOwnIC_try_megamorphic");
4200 Branch(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant()),
4201 &no_feedback, &try_polymorphic_name);
4202 }
4203
4204 BIND(&no_feedback);
4205 {
4206 TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kDefineKeyedOwnIC_Megamorphic, p->context(),
4207 p->receiver(), p->name(), p->value());
4208 }
4209
4210 BIND(&try_polymorphic_name);
4211 {
4212 // We might have a name in feedback, and a fixed array in the next slot.
4213 Comment("DefineKeyedOwnIC_try_polymorphic_name");
4214 GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, p->name()), &miss);
4215 // If the name comparison succeeded, we know we have a feedback vector
4216 // with at least one map/handler pair.
4217 TNode<MaybeObject> feedback_element =
4218 LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(p->vector()), p->slot(), kTaggedSize);
4219 TNode<WeakFixedArray> array = CAST(feedback_element);
4220 HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_receiver_map, array, &if_handler, &var_handler,
4221 &miss);
4222 }
4223 }
4224 BIND(&miss);
4225 {
4226 Comment("DefineKeyedOwnIC_miss");
4227 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kDefineKeyedOwnIC_Miss, p->context(), p->value(),
4228 p->slot(), p->vector(), p->receiver(), p->name());
4229 }
4230}
4231
4232void AccessorAssembler::StoreInArrayLiteralIC(const StoreICParameters* p) {
4233 Label miss(this, Label::kDeferred), no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred);
4234 {
4235 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
4236
4237 Label if_handler(this, &var_handler),
4238 try_polymorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
4239 try_megamorphic(this, Label::kDeferred);
4240
4241 TNode<Map> array_map = LoadReceiverMap(p->receiver());
4242 GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(array_map), &miss);
4243
4244 GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &no_feedback);
4245
4246 TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_array_map = MakeWeak(array_map);
4247 TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback =
4248 TryMonomorphicCase(p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_array_map,
4249 &if_handler, &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
4250
4251 BIND(&if_handler);
4252 {
4253 Comment("StoreInArrayLiteralIC_if_handler");
4254 // This is a stripped-down version of HandleStoreICHandlerCase.
4255 Label if_transitioning_element_store(this), if_smi_handler(this);
4256
4257 // Check used to identify the Slow case.
4258 // Currently only the Slow case uses a Smi handler.
4259 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(var_handler.value()), &if_smi_handler);
4260
4261 TNode<HeapObject> handler = CAST(var_handler.value());
4262 GotoIfNot(IsCode(handler), &if_transitioning_element_store);
4263
4264 {
4265 // Call the handler.
4266 TNode<Code> code_handler = CAST(handler);
4267 TailCallStub(StoreWithVectorDescriptor{}, code_handler, p->context(),
4268 p->receiver(), p->name(), p->value(), p->slot(),
4269 p->vector());
4270 }
4271
4272 BIND(&if_transitioning_element_store);
4273 {
4274 TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_transition_map =
4275 LoadHandlerDataField(CAST(handler), 1);
4276 TNode<Map> transition_map =
4277 CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_transition_map, &miss));
4278 GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(transition_map), &miss);
4279 TNode<Code> code =
4280 CAST(LoadObjectField(handler, StoreHandler::kSmiHandlerOffset));
4281 TailCallStub(StoreTransitionDescriptor{}, code, p->context(),
4282 p->receiver(), p->name(), transition_map, p->value(),
4283 p->slot(), p->vector());
4284 }
4285
4286 BIND(&if_smi_handler);
4287 {
4288#ifdef DEBUG
4289 // A check to ensure that no other Smi handler uses this path.
4290 TNode<Int32T> handler_word = SmiToInt32(CAST(var_handler.value()));
4291 TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind =
4292 DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word);
4293 CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kSlow)));
4294#endif
4295
4296 Comment("StoreInArrayLiteralIC_Slow");
4297 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreInArrayLiteralIC_Slow, p->context(),
4298 p->value(), p->receiver(), p->name());
4299 }
4300 }
4301
4302 BIND(&try_polymorphic);
4303 TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
4304 {
4305 Comment("StoreInArrayLiteralIC_try_polymorphic");
4306 GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)),
4307 &try_megamorphic);
4308 HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_array_map, CAST(strong_feedback), &if_handler,
4309 &var_handler, &miss);
4310 }
4311
4312 BIND(&try_megamorphic);
4313 {
4314 Comment("StoreInArrayLiteralIC_try_megamorphic");
4315 CSA_DCHECK(
4316 this,
4317 Word32Or(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, UninitializedSymbolConstant()),
4318 TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant())));
4319 GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant()),
4320 &miss);
4321 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreInArrayLiteralIC_Slow, p->context(),
4322 p->value(), p->receiver(), p->name());
4323 }
4324 }
4325
4326 BIND(&no_feedback);
4327 {
4328 Comment("StoreInArrayLiteralIC_NoFeedback");
4329 TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCreateDataProperty, p->context(), p->receiver(),
4330 p->name(), p->value());
4331 }
4332
4333 BIND(&miss);
4334 {
4335 Comment("StoreInArrayLiteralIC_miss");
4336 TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreInArrayLiteralIC_Miss, p->context(),
4337 p->value(), p->slot(), p->vector(), p->receiver(),
4338 p->name());
4339 }
4340}

4357void AccessorAssembler::GenerateLoadIC_Megamorphic() {
4358 using Descriptor = LoadWithVectorDescriptor;
4359
4360 auto receiver = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kReceiver);
4361 auto name = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kName);
4362 auto slot = Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kSlot);
4363 auto vector = Parameter<HeapObject>(Descriptor::kVector);
4364 auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
4365
4366 ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
4367 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
4368 Label if_handler(this, &var_handler), miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
4369
4370 CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedEqual(LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(vector), slot),
4371 MegamorphicSymbolConstant()));

4374 &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
4375
4376 BIND(&if_handler);

4378 // lazy_context
4379 [=] { return context; }, receiver,
4380 // lazy_name
4381 [=] { return name; },
4382 // lazy_slot
4383 [=] { return slot; }, vector);
4384 HandleLoadICHandlerCase(&p, var_handler.value(), &miss, &direct_exit);
4385
4386 BIND(&miss);
4387 direct_exit.ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadIC_Miss, context, receiver, name,
4388 slot, vector);
4389}

4556void AccessorAssembler::LookupContext(LazyNode<Object> lazy_name,
4557 TNode<TaggedIndex> depth,
4558 LazyNode<TaggedIndex> lazy_slot,
4559 TNode<Context> context,
4560 TypeofMode typeof_mode,
4561 ContextKind context_kind) {
4562 Label slowpath(this, Label::kDeferred);
4563
4564 // Check for context extensions to allow the fast path.
4565 TNode<Context> slot_context = GotoIfHasContextExtensionUpToDepth(
4566 context, Unsigned(TruncateWordToInt32(TaggedIndexToIntPtr(depth))),
4567 &slowpath);
4568
4569 // Fast path does a normal load context.
4570 {
4571 auto slot = lazy_slot();
4572 Return(
4573 context_kind == ContextKind::kScriptContext
4574 ? LoadScriptContextElement(slot_context, TaggedIndexToIntPtr(slot))
4575 : LoadContextElement(slot_context, TaggedIndexToIntPtr(slot)));
4576 }
4577
4578 // Slow path when we have to call out to the runtime.
4579 BIND(&slowpath);
4580 {
4581 auto name = lazy_name();
4582 Runtime::FunctionId function_id = typeof_mode == TypeofMode::kInside
4583 ? Runtime::kLoadLookupSlotInsideTypeof
4584 : Runtime::kLoadLookupSlot;
4585 TailCallRuntime(function_id, context, name);
4586 }
4587}
4588
4589void AccessorAssembler::GenerateLookupContextTrampoline(
4590 TypeofMode typeof_mode, ContextKind context_kind) {
4591 using Descriptor = LookupTrampolineDescriptor;
4592 LookupContext([&] { return Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kName); },
4593 Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kDepth),
4594 [&] { return Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kSlot); },
4595 Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext), typeof_mode,
4596 context_kind);
4597}

4675void AccessorAssembler::GenerateEnumeratedKeyedLoadIC() {
4676 using Descriptor = EnumeratedKeyedLoadDescriptor;
4677
4678 auto receiver = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kReceiver);
4679 auto name = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kName);
4680 auto enum_index = Parameter<Smi>(Descriptor::kEnumIndex);
4681 auto cache_type = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kCacheType);
4682 auto slot = Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kSlot);
4683 auto vector = Parameter<HeapObject>(Descriptor::kVector);
4684 auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
4685 auto lookup_start_object = std::nullopt;
4686

4825void AccessorAssembler::GenerateStoreIC_Megamorphic() {
4826 using Descriptor = StoreWithVectorDescriptor;
4827
4828 auto receiver = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kReceiver);
4829 auto name = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kName);
4830 auto value = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kValue);
4831 auto flags = std::nullopt;
4832 auto slot = Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kSlot);
4833 auto vector = Parameter<HeapObject>(Descriptor::kVector);
4834 auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
4835
4836 ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
4837 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
4838 Label if_handler(this, &var_handler), miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
4839
4840 CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedEqual(LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(vector), slot),
4841 MegamorphicSymbolConstant()));
4842
4843 TryProbeStubCache(isolate()->store_stub_cache(), receiver, CAST(name),
4844 &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
4845
4846 BIND(&if_handler);
4847 {
4848 StoreICParameters p(context, receiver, name, value, flags, slot, vector,
4849 StoreICMode::kDefault);
4850 HandleStoreICHandlerCase(&p, var_handler.value(), &miss,
4851 ICMode::kNonGlobalIC);
4852 }
4853
4854 BIND(&miss);
4855 {
4856 direct_exit.ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreIC_Miss, context, value, slot,
4857 vector, receiver, name);
4858 }
4859}

5083
5084void AccessorAssembler::GenerateCloneObjectIC_Slow() {
5085 using Descriptor = CloneObjectWithVectorDescriptor;
5086 auto source = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kSource);
5087 auto flags = Parameter<Smi>(Descriptor::kFlags);
5088 auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
5089
5090 // The CloneObjectIC_Slow implementation uses the same call interface as
5091 // CloneObjectIC, so that it can be tail called from it. However, the feedback
5092 // slot and vector are not used.
5093
5094 // First try a fast case where we copy the properties with a CSA loop.
5095 Label try_fast_case(this), call_runtime(this, Label::kDeferred);
5096
5097 // For SMIs and non JSObjects we use 0 in object properties.
5098 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, number_of_properties, IntPtrConstant(0));
5099 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(source), &try_fast_case);
5100 {
5101 TNode<Map> source_map = LoadMap(CAST(source));
5102 // We still want to stay in the semi-fast case for oddballs, strings,
5103 // proxies and such. Therefore we continue here, but using 0 in object
5104 // properties.
5105 GotoIfNot(IsJSObjectMap(source_map), &try_fast_case);
5106
5107 // At this point we don't know yet if ForEachEnumerableOwnProperty can
5108 // handle the source object. In case it is a dictionary mode object or has
5109 // non simple properties the latter will bail to `runtime_copy`. For code
5110 // compactness we don't check it here, assuming that the number of in-object
5111 // properties is set to 0 (or a reasonable value).
5112 number_of_properties = MapUsedInObjectProperties(source_map);
5113 GotoIf(IntPtrGreaterThanOrEqual(number_of_properties.value(),
5114 IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kMapCacheSize)),
5115 &call_runtime);
5116 }
5117 Goto(&try_fast_case);
5118
5119 BIND(&try_fast_case);
5120 TNode<NativeContext> native_context = LoadNativeContext(context);
5121 TNode<Map> initial_map = LoadCachedMap(
5122 native_context, number_of_properties.value(), &call_runtime);
5123 TNode<JSObject> result = AllocateJSObjectFromMap(initial_map);
5124
5125 // Handle the case where the object literal overrides the prototype.
5126 {
5127 Label did_set_proto_if_needed(this);
5128 TNode<BoolT> is_null_proto = SmiNotEqual(
5129 SmiAnd(flags, SmiConstant(ObjectLiteral::kHasNullPrototype)),
5130 SmiConstant(Smi::zero()));
5131 GotoIfNot(is_null_proto, &did_set_proto_if_needed);
5132
5133 CallRuntime(Runtime::kInternalSetPrototype, context, result,
5134 NullConstant());
5135
5136 Goto(&did_set_proto_if_needed);
5137 BIND(&did_set_proto_if_needed);
5138 }
5139
5140 // Early return for when we know there are no properties.
5141 ReturnIf(TaggedIsSmi(source), result);
5142 ReturnIf(IsNullOrUndefined(source), result);
5143
5144 Label runtime_copy(this, Label::kDeferred);
5145
5146 TNode<Map> source_map = LoadMap(CAST(source));
5147 GotoIfNot(IsJSObjectMap(source_map), &runtime_copy);
5148 // Takes care of objects with elements.
5149 GotoIfNot(IsEmptyFixedArray(LoadElements(CAST(source))), &runtime_copy);
5150
5151 // TODO(olivf, chrome:1204540) This can still be several times slower than the
5152 // Babel translation. TF uses FastGetOwnValuesOrEntries -- should we do sth
5153 // similar here?
5154 ForEachEnumerableOwnProperty(
5155 context, source_map, CAST(source), kPropertyAdditionOrder,
5156 [=, this](TNode<Name> key, LazyNode<Object> value) {
5157 CreateDataProperty(context, result, key, value());
5158 },
5159 &runtime_copy);
5160 Return(result);
5161
5162 // This is the fall-back case for the above fastcase, where we allocated an
5163 // object, but failed to copy the properties in CSA.
5164 BIND(&runtime_copy);
5165 CallRuntime(Runtime::kCopyDataProperties, context, result, source);
5166 Return(result);
5167
5168 // Final fallback is to call into the runtime version.
5169 BIND(&call_runtime);
5170 Return(CallRuntime(Runtime::kCloneObjectIC_Slow, context, source, flags));
5171}

5174 using Descriptor = CloneObjectBaselineDescriptor;
5175
5176 auto source = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kSource);
5177 auto flags = Parameter<Smi>(Descriptor::kFlags);
5178 auto slot = Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kSlot);
5179

5181 TNode<Context> context = LoadContextFromBaseline();

5186
5187void AccessorAssembler::GenerateCloneObjectIC() {
5188 using Descriptor = CloneObjectWithVectorDescriptor;
5189 auto source = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kSource);
5190 auto flags = Parameter<Smi>(Descriptor::kFlags);
5191 auto slot = Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kSlot);
5192 auto maybe_vector = Parameter<HeapObject>(Descriptor::kVector);
5193 auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
5194 TVARIABLE(Map, result_map);
5195 Label if_result_map(this, &result_map), if_empty_object(this),
5196 miss(this, Label::kDeferred), try_polymorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
5197 try_megamorphic(this, Label::kDeferred), slow(this, Label::kDeferred);
5198
5199 TNode<Map> source_map = LoadReceiverMap(source);
5200 GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(source_map), &miss);
5201
5202 GotoIf(IsUndefined(maybe_vector), &miss);
5203
5204 TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback;
5205 TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_source_map = MakeWeak(source_map);
5206
5207 // Decide if monomorphic or polymorphic, then dispatch based on the handler.
5208 {
5209 TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
5210 Label if_handler(this, &var_handler);
5211 feedback = TryMonomorphicCase(slot, CAST(maybe_vector), weak_source_map,
5212 &if_handler, &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
5213
5214 BIND(&try_polymorphic);
5215 TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
5216 {
5217 Comment("CloneObjectIC_try_polymorphic");
5218 GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)),
5219 &try_megamorphic);
5220 HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_source_map, CAST(strong_feedback), &if_handler,
5221 &var_handler, &miss);
5222 }
5223
5224 BIND(&try_megamorphic);
5225 {
5226 Comment("CloneObjectIC_try_megamorphic");
5227 CSA_DCHECK(
5228 this,
5229 Word32Or(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, UninitializedSymbolConstant()),
5230 TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant())));
5231 GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant()),
5232 &miss);
5233 Goto(&slow);
5234 }
5235
5236 BIND(&if_handler);
5237 Comment("CloneObjectIC_if_handler");
5238
5239 // When the result of cloning the object is an empty object literal we store
5240 // a Smi into the feedback.
5241 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(var_handler.value()), &if_empty_object);
5242
5243 // Handlers for the CloneObjectIC stub are weak references to the Map of
5244 // a result object.
5245 result_map = CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(var_handler.value(), &miss));
5246 GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(result_map.value()), &miss);
5247 Goto(&if_result_map);
5248 }
5249
5250 // Cloning with a concrete result_map.
5251 {
5252 BIND(&if_result_map);
5253 Comment("CloneObjectIC_if_result_map");
5254
5255 TNode<Object> object = FastCloneJSObject(
5256 CAST(source), source_map, result_map.value(),
5257 [&](TNode<Map> map, TNode<HeapObject> properties,
5258 TNode<FixedArray> elements) {
5259 return UncheckedCast<JSObject>(AllocateJSObjectFromMap(
5260 map, properties, elements, AllocationFlag::kNone,
5261 SlackTrackingMode::kDontInitializeInObjectProperties));
5262 },
5263 true /* target_is_new */);
5264
5265 Return(object);
5266 }
5267
5268 // Case for when the result is the empty object literal. Can't be shared with
5269 // the above since we must initialize the in-object properties.
5270 {
5271 BIND(&if_empty_object);
5272 Comment("CloneObjectIC_if_empty_object");
5273 TNode<NativeContext> native_context = LoadNativeContext(context);
5274 TNode<Map> initial_map = LoadObjectFunctionInitialMap(native_context);
5275 TNode<JSObject> object =
5276 UncheckedCast<JSObject>(AllocateJSObjectFromMap(initial_map, {}, {}));
5277 Return(object);
5278 }
5279
5280 BIND(&slow);
5281 {
5282 TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCloneObjectIC_Slow, context, source, flags, slot,
5283 maybe_vector);
5284 }
5285
5286 BIND(&miss);
5287 {
5288 Comment("CloneObjectIC_miss");
5289 TNode<HeapObject> map_or_result =
5290 CAST(CallRuntime(Runtime::kCloneObjectIC_Miss, context, source, flags,
5291 slot, maybe_vector));
5292 Label restart(this);
5293 GotoIf(IsMap(map_or_result), &restart);
5294 CSA_DCHECK(this, IsJSObject(map_or_result));
5295 Return(map_or_result);
5296
5297 BIND(&restart);
5298 result_map = CAST(map_or_result);
5299 Goto(&if_result_map);
5300 }
5301}

5305

5308 auto slot = Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kSlot);
5309 auto vector = Parameter<HeapObject>(Descriptor::kVector);
5310 auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
5311
5312 LoadICParameters p(context, receiver, name, slot, vector);
5313 KeyedLoadIC(&p, LoadAccessMode::kHas);
5314}

5351
5352void AccessorAssembler::BranchIfPrototypesHaveNoElements(
5353 TNode<Map> receiver_map, Label* definitely_no_elements,
5354 Label* possibly_elements) {
5355 TVARIABLE(Map, var_map, receiver_map);
5356 Label loop_body(this, &var_map);
5357 TNode<FixedArray> empty_fixed_array = EmptyFixedArrayConstant();
5358 TNode<NumberDictionary> empty_slow_element_dictionary =
5359 EmptySlowElementDictionaryConstant();
5360 Goto(&loop_body);
5361
5362 BIND(&loop_body);
5363 {
5364 TNode<Map> map = var_map.value();
5365 TNode<HeapObject> prototype = LoadMapPrototype(map);
5366 GotoIf(IsNull(prototype), definitely_no_elements);
5367 TNode<Map> prototype_map = LoadMap(prototype);
5368 TNode<Uint16T> prototype_instance_type = LoadMapInstanceType(prototype_map);
5369
5370 // Pessimistically assume elements if a Proxy, Special API Object,
5371 // or JSPrimitiveWrapper wrapper is found on the prototype chain. After this
5372 // instance type check, it's not necessary to check for interceptors or
5373 // access checks.
5374 Label if_custom(this, Label::kDeferred), if_notcustom(this);
5375 Branch(IsCustomElementsReceiverInstanceType(prototype_instance_type),
5376 &if_custom, &if_notcustom);
5377
5378 BIND(&if_custom);
5379 {
5380 // For string JSPrimitiveWrapper wrappers we still support the checks as
5381 // long as they wrap the empty string.
5382 GotoIfNot(
5383 InstanceTypeEqual(prototype_instance_type, JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE),
5384 possibly_elements);
5385 TNode<Object> prototype_value =
5386 LoadJSPrimitiveWrapperValue(CAST(prototype));
5387 Branch(IsEmptyString(prototype_value), &if_notcustom, possibly_elements);
5388 }
5389
5390 BIND(&if_notcustom);
5391 {
5392 TNode<FixedArrayBase> prototype_elements = LoadElements(CAST(prototype));
5393 var_map = prototype_map;
5394 GotoIf(TaggedEqual(prototype_elements, empty_fixed_array), &loop_body);
5395 Branch(TaggedEqual(prototype_elements, empty_slow_element_dictionary),
5396 &loop_body, possibly_elements);
5397 }
5398 }
5399}
